comment: It wasn't the cleanest bathroom, but useable. If you visit, sit upstairs on the balcony.

name: The Center Project (GLBT)
directions: Near intersection of 3rd Ave South. Look for rainbow flag in Hewitt Plaza strip mall. Be sure and pick up information on T-Time gender forum the 1st Saturday of every month, 7-9pm.

name: BP Kangeroo (24 hours)
street: Corner of Hwy 17 Bus. and 6th Ave South
directions: Kangeroo is in front of NMB Post Office. Restrooms on left as you enter.

name: Kroger (open 24 hours)
directions: Upon entering store, go to left. Restrooms are in Deli, behind seating area.
comment: Kroger in Garden City Beach is similar. Also, most Bi-Lo grocery stores here, have single stale bathrooms in their Deli depts. All here are open 24 hours with the deli's unmanned at night.

name: Bi-Lo  24 Hour Grocery
street: 38th Ave North and Hwy 17 Bypass;  Plantation Point Shop Cent.
directions: Upon entering go to Right. Single stall bathrooms are in the Deli deptment, which is unmanned at night.
comment: Most Krogers and other Bi-los in area have similar setup.

name: Dillards
street: Coastal Grand Mall,  Hwy 17 By-pass and Hwy 501
directions: Upstairs on 2nd floor. Straight out from up escalators.  Single stall and private
comment: Regular store hours till 9pm.

name: Time Out (Gay Bar)
street: Main and Oak Streets, Downtowne Myrtle Beach
directions: Near 8th Ave North and Hwy 17 Bus. Across Broadway Ave from Macfadden Music store.DO NOT PARK BEHIND BAR,you WILL be towed. Park out front or on street side of bar.
comment: Oldest Gay Bar in Myrtle Beach. Usually open from about 4pm till 2-3am. Door person will usually let you in use the restroom, depending how busy they are and if you don't look like a "street person".

name: Pan American Pancake House
directions: Across from Big Lots on south end of beach. Restrooms are in rear, inside. Just ask Connie, or anyone really, if OK.
comment: This restaurant has always been Very GLBT FRIENDLY for the last 20 years.It's where people go for a late, afterhours bite.The person that would make a negative comment towards you here,would be the one at risk. It's pretty informal, esp. at night. Be sure and say hello to dear Connie when you're there.

name: Harris Teeter Supermarket (24 hours)
directions: Go tru doors in fresh produce section.
comment: Open 24/7  Store in Mt Pleasant is good also.

name: Harris Teeter Supermarket (24 Hours)
directions: Follow signs in produce section, to the right of the store.
comment: open 24/7 & Clean.

name: Cherry Bean Gourmet Coffeehouse
directions: In the back of the coffeehouse.
comment: This is a cool, queer friendly place. You need to get a token from someone at the register to use the locking, single stall restroom.

name: Valero Station
directions: This is a gas station/convenience store across the street from a big cinema complex. There's one bathroom, gender free, a door that locks, a sink and a toilet. Walk in the front door, the bathroom's pretty much straight ahead at the back of the store.

name: P&C
directions: Go in the main door, the bathrooms are to the left near the service desk. They are gendered, but no one ever seems to watch them or care who's in them. Two large rooms with toilet, sink, handrail and locking door.
comment: Open 24 hours. Generally fairly clean.

name: Stiehl's Body Modification Station
street: 120 South Cayuga Street (South end of the Commons)
directions: Bathroom is supposed to be for customers, but the proprietors and employees are great people who are used to freaks and gender outlaws and will probably let you use the bathroom anyway if you come in and ask nicely.
comment:
Monday - Noon - 6:00 pm

Tuesday thru Saturday - Noon - 8:00pm

name: A1 Pizzeria
directions: This is a family restaurant and bar. Bathrooms are for customers, but they'll probably let you use it if you ask nicely. Come in the front door, go to the left past the desk and to the back of the room. Go through the door marked for bathrooms and there's a men's room, a women's room and a unisex handicap room. All three are single rooms with toilet, sink and locking door.

name: Laval's Multiculturelle Public Library
street: 1535 Chomedey Blvd. (Between St. Martin and Souvenir blvd.)
directions: There are two restroom, one upstairs and the other one on the main floor.
comment:
Usually open from noon to 9:00 pm.



Because it's a municipal building, the opening hours are kinna weird!

name: Polyclinique Medicale Concorde
street: 300 de la Concorde East Blvd. H7G 2E6
directions: There is at least one restroom on each floor.
comment: I don't know the opening hours.

name: Hess Express
directions: Straight back from the door.
comment: Open till 11pm?

name: Taylor's Mini Mart
directions: Straight back from the door.
comment: Right off the Richmondville exit of I-88

name: Collegetown Bagels
directions: Go all the way to the back of the restaurant, follow the narrow hallway on the right hand side, back even farther.
comment: Open Mon-Sat, 7am-7:30pm; Sun, 7am-5pm. Bathrooms are small but private. They don't care if you buy anything or just come in to pee.

name: Leather Bound
street: 96 Front Street (near corner of Front & Main)
directions: Downstairs. You have to ask for the key.
comment: I don't remember whether it's gendered or not, but Leather Bound caters to transwomen and crossdressers and is a friendly and safe place.

name: Cole Coffee
directions: The coffee shop is on the corner and has two entrances -enter from the 63rd street entrance and the door to the bathroom is dead ahead.
comment: If it is locked, the key is on the metal frame of a french press on the counter.  The coffee is somewhere between freebasing and rocket fuel if you want to take it for a spin ;-)

name: Adagio Cafe
comment: Super nice and clean!

name: NewBreak Coffee
directions: in the back.
comment: it's token operated, so you have to buy something to get a token. the place has a great tea selection!

name: Urban Grind
directions: there are two bathrooms, labeled bathroom 1 and bathroom 2.
comment: not sure if bathrooms are accessible. bathroom one has a one way mirror, so it's kinda freaky

name: T-Deli
directions: straight in, visible from the street. single stall gender neutral accessible bathroom.

name: Lucky Buck's
directions: visible from the street, single stall gender neutral and accessible.

name: Pokez
directions: in the saloon doors through the kitchen. two single stall gendered bathrooms.
comment: punk rock and amazing vegan burritos. give this place a try, they probably won't bug you about the bathroom.

name: Oakland Airport
directions: by gate 26,27,28, in the southwest area. a family bathroom next to two gendered bathrooms.
comment: you'll need to be flying to use this as it is within the terminal.

name: San Diego International Airport
directions: by the security checkpoint, entrance to the southwest airlines terminal there is a family bathroom between two traditionally gendered options
comment: this bathroom is outside of the gate/security area. there only appear to be gendered options within the terminal itself!

name: Rancho's
directions: in the rear of the place there are two single gendered stalls.

name: Coffee House Cafe

directions: If you enter from the take-out entrance, turn to your right. From the bar entrance, turn left. The 2 gender neutral, single stall bathrooms are on the hallway between entrances.
comment:
Mon-Wed 4 pm - 10 pm

Thu-Fri 4 pm - 3:30 am

Sat 11 am - 3:30 am

Sun 11 am - 8 pm

(714) 680-5400

name: factory direct home furnishings
directions: In the back, just tell the staff that nature calls.

name: Madoka Restaurant/Bainbridge Island, WA
directions: first floor, back around the bar, 2 ungendered locking restrooms
comment: our favorite restaurant

name: Mall of NH
directions: near Best Buy, and near Spencer's Gift's, follow signs
comment:
Mall hours 8:30 to 9:30 pm mon-sat

sun - 11-6pm

Shopping hours 10:00 am to 9:30 pm mon-sat

11-6pm

name: Kohls (U-Mall)
directions: Back by the customer service desk there are three doors to bathrooms- one to a womens room, one to a mens room, and one to a single seater for either gender and wheelchair accessible

name: M Bar
directions: On the first floor in the hallway between the main bar room and the VIP section.

name: Bridgewater commons Mall
comment: This is a uni gender restroom if ... it remains unlocked!

directions: Right off of the Cornelius Pass Rd exit of Highway 26. Gender neutral bathroom in between M and F bathrooms, near pharmacy.
comment: Hours: 7am to 11pm 7 days a week

directions: Two single seater bathrooms for any gender

name: The Bean
comment: Sign says you have to be a paying customer, but you do not need to ask for a key.

There is an elevator.

10 am - 7 pm, Mon. - Thurs.

10 am - 5 pm, Sat.

504-596-3100

name: Gainesville, GA / Belk (Housewares Dept) inside Lakeshore Mall
directions: There are 2 Belks in this mall... you are looking for the one with the men\'s, kid\'s, and housewares.  The restroom is located in an area near the bedding.  There are also traditional bathrooms, but there is 1 unisex/handicap bathroom with its own door and lock.
inside the resturant grubsteak, next to tattoo shop
comment: two genderfree bathrooms, for customers only,but the guys there are nice and i bet they wouldn't mind if you used it, puls it gets busy and i think not alot of them would even know.

name: Grubsteak
directions: inside the resturant grubsteak, next to tattoo shop
comment: open till 4 am!!

name: Value Village
directions: Ask for key at front desk, bathroom is on the right from the entrance.
comment: I don't know *how* accessible this makes it, but it's the largest single-toilet bathroom I've ever seen in my life - roomy and spacious, could be a bedroom. Open til 9 most days? 6 or 7 on Sundays.

name: Del Vecchios
directions:
They are located in the second half of the restaurant.

When you walk in, go to the right, through a set of doors on your left, and immediately turn to right after going through the doors.
comment:
I haven't had any issues with this diner, and I eat/use the restrooms here somewhat-often.

I'm not sure if they require you to be a paying customer, but it's definitely worth the dine-in, even for a small dish.

It's a great and quiet place.

Or you could always ask if you have to dine in.

Hello. We are in process of renovating a gorgeous 1920 building into an Art Lounge here in St. Petersburg and our plan is to create a single 'bathroom' where every stall has a toilet which is enclosed in it's own small room. Complete privacy for everyone.  Then everyone shares the 4 sinks and "primping" area.  This will be a classy modern art gallery mashed together with a swanky lounge. I've seen this type of bath setup all over Europe and am going to use it here.  But the city is giving me a headache about it.  Can you please offer any advice or comments to help us along?  Much thanks and good luck to us all!  Michael  :-)lrn2thnk@tampabay.rr.com

name: University of San Diego
directions: All the buildings have restrooms that get cleaned everyday.
comment: When you drive in ask for a visitor pass.

name: Subway Sandwiches
directions: enter on sutter st at polk. go left. single stall gender neutral and accessible!

name: la croissointerie
street: ste catherine west of guy about 6 blocks - (sorry, i can't find the exact address online) on the north side of the street, cafe with green awning
comment:
there are 2 washrooms, both gendered, at the back, but its very discreet, quiet and single bathrooms. i've never had problems using either the mens or womens. 



the cafe itself is usually busy with students, so if you go in acting like you're looking for someone, or just act casually, and go all the way to the back, it's never a problem. the people that work there are really relaxed and friendly, too.

name: 2110 Concordia Centre for Gender Advocacy
directions:
right next to le frigo vert

walk into 2110 mackay, there's a hallway and 2 doors, one on the left one on the right - the one on the left is the 2110 (there are signs everywhere) - totally 100% accessible, everyone welcome, you can come just to use the washroom, too
comment: open mon-thursday 12-5 and 12-6pm....ofen open a wee later for events

name: Belgo Building
directions:
some of the washrooms on some of the floors of the building are handicap, some are so empty and relaxed it seems like anyone can walk in - there are a few that say things like "women" and aren't single stalled, but the signs are painted over so much it feels like they're probably for whoever. 



go into the main entrance and either up the stairs in front of you, or to the left to get to the elevators
comment:
good bet if you're in that area of downtown - often open, good hours

-chill arts gallery building, people are relaxed and don't pay any attention to each other, really

name: LGCCNO
directions: 1st Floor Available when the center is open.  Phone (504) 945-1103 to see if they are open.

name: Primrose Café

comment: 2 gendered stalls, marked M and F. Staff heard to comment 'go in either, they're both the same anyway'. Probably need to look like you could be a paying customer.

name: Al Taib
street: on guy just south of ste.catherine on the east side of the street,
directions: one of 3 locations of al taib downtown at concordia - best for washroom facilities - southeast side of guy almost right on corner of guy+ste catherine
comment: small single genderfree washroom to the right of the till, really clean, nice, people friendly, and you have to buy a water and that's it (sometimes you can go in and use it if it's busy, like during lunch)

name: Boston Tea Party Café
directions: In the back
comment: Door to stalls marked with usual gendered symbols, but stalls themselves unmarked. Probably need to look like you could be a paying customer.

name: Le Baobab
directions: Rear of the restaurant.
comment: One single-stall locking bathroom. This cafe serves fair-trade coffee and sells it in bulk (for cheaper than the supermarket) and offers free Wifi. Corner of 3e Avenue and rue Wellington in Verdun. De L'Eglise metro.

name: Missouri Lounge
directions: First floor, in the back
comment: Cool bar, open 'til 2 am

Walk through the front doors, go towards the elevator in the lobby, just past it on the right is a single genderfree washroom. Also in between the Melody Bar and the Art Bar is another genderfree single stall, as well as a genderfree washroom with two separate stalls inside.



For an accessible washroom go up the ramp and into the Melody Bar, through the bar and take a left to get into the lobby. The single stall washroom there is accessible.
comment: Always open. If it's the middle of the night  the front desk person will probably want to know what you're doing there.

1) There is one single stall washroom in the classroom on the main floor (normally ok to use if there's not a class happening)

2) A single stall on the second floor there is a conference room (same thing as before...if nothings going on okay to use)

3) A single stall on the 4th floor at the Reading Room

name: Monopole

comment: Open 5pm-2am; if you were to stop in Plattsburgh at least once in your life, the Monopole is pretty much THE bar you would want to hang out at. Very chill atmosphere; dudes and girls share the same bathroom and everyone's cool with that. Though some people in the North Country are incredulous at the thought: "OMG I can't believe this is a shared bathroom!" But they get over it.

name: Allen County Public Library

name: Meijer's

comment: It's not really open to the public, but if there is an event going on that you are attending, the bathrooms are great - private, non-gendered, and accessable.  There's even an elevator to the second floor.  It would be a good place to rent out (cheap) for a meeting or event.

name: UNC-CH Campus Mitchel Hall

name: JIFFI STOP

JIFFI STOP - Michigan Public Rest Area.

South-West corner of M6 and Kalamazoo Avenue.
comment: JIFFI is an acronym for Jons Installed at Fast Freeway Intersections. JIFFI is an interesting design, being embedded right into the corner of the M6-Kalamazoo bridge abuttment.  JIFFI also offers the added convenience of wireless Internet access.

name: The Crepe House
directions: In the back corner of the restaurant, to the left when entering.
comment: Make a beeline to the restroom if you're not eating there, there's a little hall you can wait in if it is occupied.

name: YMCA Berkeley - Gym
directions: The single-stall bathroom, once you're in the building, is on the same floor as the entrance.  There may be another one on a different floor as well.
comment: This resource is mostly for gym members.  If you aren't a member, it might take explaining yourself, but the staff are usually pretty kind.

name: La Paloma Sabanera
directions: In the back, past the food counter
comment: Often closes by 530 or 6 pm. Is close to the Capital and legislative buildings. About 20 minute walk from downtown Hartford. Trans Friendly.

name: Cafe Mediterraneum
directions: Get the key at the counter; up the stairs and to your left.

name: Moe's
directions: On the third floor.  You need a token from the cashier's desk.

name: Polynesian Beach & Golf Resort
directions: go into lobby into next room its the second door on the left.

name: Wal-Mart
directions: Located at the back middle of the store by shoes.
comment: There are men's, women's, and family bathrooms.  The family bathroom is a large single locking bathroom.

name: The Barbeque Joint
directions: Walk in and it's directly to the left.

name: California Adventure - Bugs Land
directions: In the 'Bugs land' in california Adventure, there is a 'family' restroom which is not gendered.
comment: Some non-gendered bathrooms are in place throughout the park.

name: UNC, Peabody Hall
street: UNC,School of Education,  CB# 3500, Peabody Hall
directions: Enter the building through the main entrance, which is on Cameron Avenue. On the first floor there is a gender neutral bathroom on your right when you past the elevator.

name: Padgett Station
directions: Go through the door way past the coffee bean shelf and there are two individual restrooms.
comment:
Monday - Thursday 9:00 am - 11:00 pm  

Friday - Saturday  9:00 am - midnight 

Sunday  9:00 am - 5:00 pm

name: Uncommon Grounds Cafe
directions: Enter cafe and turn left.  There is a door along the wall to your left, go through it, the bathroom is gender free and child friendly on your right.
comment: This is a small queer friendly cafe.  It isn't always busy so you might feel more comfortable buying a coffee after using their restroom - but it's probably not a requirement.

name: Hartman's Independent Grocers
directions: Ask for a key.

name: Brewster Town Hall
directions: Single bathrooms inside rear entrance next to tourist information center.

name: Cineplex Galaxy
directions: Two accessible washrooms are available on either side of the multiplex. Staff can direct you to them once you show them a movie ticket.
comment: This tends to be the busiest movie theatre complex in Canada, so don't be surprised if they're occupied on a Friday or Saturday night.

name: East Coast Bar
directions: straight shot from front door all the way to the back of the bar, right and left doors are bathrooms (center door leads to outside).
comment: Both are very large locking bathrooms, single person, one door, non-gendered. This is a bar, so you should buy something, even a soda or water, and there is a possibility you will be asked for id to verify you are 21. Staff is mostly gay friendly, patrons are so-so, but I have never had trouble.

name: Ben and Jerry's
directions: upper level, where the counter is.

name: Rhode Island College, Gaige Hall
directions: Second floor in the left wing.  There are two women's bathrooms, one men's and one non-gendered, all single stall.

name: Beaver Cafe
directions: At the back of the restaurant there are two genderfree singe washrooms. Not wheelchair accessible, about half a dozen stairs to go up.
comment: Yes, it's a restaurant so it normally might be weird to walk in to use the washroom, but since they're very trans friendly they would probably be very understanding of someone needing to pee in a safe space.

name: Bay Park Square Mall
directions: In Food Court
comment: Family restroom

name: King Solomon's Reef
directions: This bathroom is inside the old card room. Just ask a server to use it.

name: Hanover Inn
directions: Take the elevator or stairs up to the first floor, then follow the signs for 'Public Restroom'.

name: Lou's Restaurant
directions: Walk along the counter to the back, through the doors to the kitchen, then down the stairs on your left.  Two bathrooms, both genderfree.

name: Juliano's
directions: All the way in the back of the resturaunt.
comment: This place has the advantage of weird hours (open to 1:30 am or 3:00 am depending on the day), but due to it's size it's impossible to slip in and out unnoticed just to use the bathroom... Not that you'd want to though, once you smelled the pizza.

name: Baker Library
directions: Go into the stacks (open) and take the stairs or elevator to the sixth floor.  The restroom is near the elevator.

name: Athletic Centre
directions: Go through the turnstyles at the equipment desk, down the stairs, make a left at the bottom, walk past the sports medicine clinic and they'll be on your right before you hit the pool.
comment: ok you need a pass or student id to get in, but you can sweet talk the equipment desk guys to let you in if you're savvy.

name: Lettieri Espresso and Bar
directions: Hidden by a pillar, all the way in the back.
comment: It's a lounge-y cafe, i cant see people questioning you if you just went in to use the washroom (and not to buy anything). Right in the village so there is usually less gender scrutiny.

name: Hanover Food Coop
directions: Go straight through the entryway, then down the short corridor on your right, before the Produce section.  2 genderfree bathrooms.
comment: 8am-8pm (I think), closed on major holidays.

name: Lebanon Food Coop
directions: Go through the entrance, straight past the info desk, then turn right at the Cafe and down the hall past the counter.  The bathroom is on the left.
comment: 7am-9pm, except major holidays

name: Norwich Inn
directions: There's one bathroom at the far end of the tavern (Jasper Murdock's Alehouse), and one off the lobby.

name: Nugget Movie Theater
directions: Past the ticket booth and concession stand, at the end of the lobby.

name: Starbucks
directions: If you're facing the counter, it's to the right of the bar and in the back of the building
comment: Staff is very open-minded and trans positive. Bathrooms are around a corner and kind of "hidden", so if you're nervous about people seeing you go in/out you're safe.

name: UBC Student Union Building
directions: North side of the second floor of the SUB

name: Pasta Bangs!
directions: One single stall, non-gendered bathroom in rear of restaurant.
comment: Website: http://www.pastabangs.com/

name: Phoenix (Sky Harbor) Airport
directions: Family/Companion restroom across from gate C17.  I think there may be one at the beginning of each terminal, but I was only in terminal C.

name: Just Fresh
directions: Towards the rear of the restaurant, near where you pick up your orders.
comment:
Website - http://www.justfresh.com/



Open Mon-Fri 7 AM - 5 PM

name: Bare Bones Cafe
directions: 2 Single-Stall Gender-Neutral Bathrooms (labeled as such) in rear of coffee shop
comment: Website: http://www.muddywatersportland.com/

name: Baked in Kansas City
directions: Back towards the kitchen, take a left.

name: york university
directions: first floor, by the bakery/shwarma shop
comment: and oh its spacious!

name: Play Louisville
directions: In the lounge area, second right after entering building
comment: May have to pay a cover to enter depending on the night.

name: Governors Square Mall
directions: Near food court

name: Safeway
directions: Walk in on the left entrance and turn to the left 90 degrees. Wlk down the hallway a little bit and there will be two bathrooms: one for men and one for woman.
comment: Almost always open from 6:00 AM to 12:00 midnight except for holidays.

name: TriCounty Mall
directions: First floor of the mall, near the store entrance to Macy's. It is a single-user lockable 'family' restroom off a small hallway kitty-corner from the  fountain and furniture area.
comment: Official hours are M-S 10-9, Sun 12-6, though the mall doors are generally open for an hour or two before and after the "official" hours.

name: Starbucks
directions: In the back of the store
comment: Don't require a key, baristas are nice and don't care if you don't buy something. Two bathrooms- both single occupant and both genderfree. Closes at 9.

name: GLBT Student Support Services office
comment:
Gay, Lesbian, Bisexual, Transgender Student Support Services

Indiana University

705 E. 7th Street

Bloomington IN 47408-3809

PH: 812-855-4252 

Fax: 812-855-4465 

http://www.indiana.edu/~glbt/ 

Open Monday through Friday  8am to 5pm

name: Mattingly Brewing
directions: It\'s on the first floor, next to the bar. Accessible entry is through the back of the building, off the parking lot.
comment: http://mattinglybrewing.com/

name: Hair Cuttery
directions: Walk straight in kind of quickly and walk towards the back. Pass the employees' lounge down the hallway that ends with a large door on the right. That is the bathroom.
comment: Jen is great for hair cuts! :]

name: Subway
directions: Walk to the back. There will be two doors. Chose one.
comment: My favorite sub is chicken terryaki w/ lettuce, tomato, onions, and sweet onion sauce toasted on hearty italtian.

name: The Ugly Mug
directions: down the back hallway
comment: it's a very small single stall bathroom. it is not wheelchair-accessible, but the entire cafe is very cool.

name: FedEx Kinko's
comment: Call the store at 203-319-0500 for hours

name: Boulder Public Library
directions: Located in the Boulder Public Library Children's Room (see comments). The library is between 9th and 11th streets and spans Boulder Creek (runs west to east) between Canyon Blvd. and Arapahoe Avenue. The Children's Room is just inside the Arapahoe Avenue entry.
comment: This is the family-use bathroom in the Boulder Public Library Children's Room, and generally used for caregivers and small children. For children's safety they require that people ask for the key, but as of May 29, 2007 the head Children's Librarian has instructed her staff that the key is to be provided to anyone who asks to use "the safe2pee bathroom." You can also simply say you are transgendered and uncomfortable using the other public bathrooms and they will provide the key.

name: Xtra Mart
directions: enter the Xtra Mart and go to the rear, left of the Xtra Mart portion of the store (Subway and Honey Dew Donuts are to the left of this) and it's the last door on left.
comment: Very clean and private

name: Mohawk Service Station
directions: Sign says "Washrooms", but when you walk through the door there is only a single non-gendered lockable washroom.
comment: Kinda dirty, but otherwise okay.

name: San Francisco Public Library - Main
directions: Bathrooms are on the lower level, behind the stairway.  If entering on Grove, go down the stairs or spiral ramp before you get to the security gates.
comment: There are two sets of bathrooms, the lower level ones described, and another set after you pass through security, just past the elevators.  Security just means you\'re not stealing any books, so no worries going through it.

name: ASU smith-wright hall
street: on campus between rankin science and the library
directions: 3rd floor, middle of the hall
comment: specifically labled as a transgender bathroom!!  our psychology department is awesome!

name: South Center Mall
directions: Restroom entrance in the food court (Best Buy entrance).  Family lounge is to the left.  There is one gender free locking bathroom on the right side of the lounge.
comment: Nice roomy bathroom with sink and mirror included inside.

name: South Center Mall
directions: Restroom entrance in the food court (Best Buy entrance).  Family lounge is to the left.  There is one gender free locking bathroom on the right side of the lounge.
comment: Nice roomy bathroom with sink and mirror included inside.

name: waffle house
directions: Go in the door and through the swinging door to the left.
comment: 24 hours, as far as i know.

name: java monkey
directions: In the back; single-stall/locking

name: Atticus Book Store
directions: main floor, back right hand corner.
comment: open until 10, I think.

name: Tazza Cafe
directions: to the left of the coffee/drinks bar area
comment: 2 genderfree, single stall, locking bathrooms.

name: Red Fez
directions: one bathroom on first floor near the kitchen. second bathroom on second floor between the bar and pinball machine
comment: 2 genderfree, single stall, locking bathrooms.

name: Hooters of Dallas
comment: Both restrooms are locking and genderfree.

name: Harvard Law School - Austin Hall
directions: walk in the main door and turn left. turn left again till you see the staircase or elevator.  go to the 3rd floor.  bathroom is on the landing.
comment: it's all law school offices near the bathroom, but the bathroom is public to the school. always clean. as long as people are  respectful of the space as a working environment and they are just in and out, it is unlikely anyone will ask any questions.

name: Martsa on Elm
comment: Tibetan restaurant. One restroom, ungen dered.

name: Humboldt State University
directions: NHE entire biulding, located next to the health at the library circle entrance.  Also genderfree at the multicultural center House 55 Laurel St.
comment: Located on a university campus, usually open until well into the evening 11pmish?

name: Little Sister's Book & Art Emporium
comment: Little Sister's is open from 10 am to 11 pm. You need to ask for the key from one of their staff.

name: King's English Bookstore
directions: First floor, near the back.

name: Utah Pride Center
directions: They are in the TINT (youth section) on the south side of the parking lot.  These bathrooms are for folks 14-20 years old.  Other gender neutral bathrooms are between the middle meeting room and multi-purpose rooms.  These are usually locked unless you are there for a meeting.  If in doubt, use the free ones in the cafe!
comment: This is just about as queer friendly as you can get..

name: The Crepe House
directions: up by the counter, one single stall gender neutral bathroom.

name: Beard Papa
directions: by the counter
comment: has one of those coded doors. you must buy something to use it :(

name: Stony Brook Union
directions: On the main floor, to the left of the information desk.
comment: This used to be an employee only bathroom, but is now a gender-neutral single occupancy bathroom open to anyone. It's occasionally still locked by mistake; if that happens just ask whoever's working the info desk to unlock it.

name: FLITE (Ferris State University's) Library
directions: It's in the basement, it might take some looking to find it.

name: Jewel-Osco
directions: Front left corner of the store, by the pharmacy.
comment: 24-hour.

name: South Campus Commons 1
directions: Next to the seminar room, across from the Capstone office
comment: Two single room unisex bathrooms. Building only accessible with campus ID outside of business hours.

name: Mother Earth's Storehouse
directions:
Enter mall, look for Mother Earth's Storehouse. There is a sign on the outside of the building - it's on the side with Modell's, to the right of Fashion Bug. 







There are two gender neutral bathrooms in the back of the store, to the right of the deli.

name: Goodwill
comment: There are two locking doors, with signs on the doors that are both male and female.  It's off of Route 29, which is what most of Charlottesville is based off of, anyway, so it's never too far from where you are.

name: Mangiare
directions: The bathroom is in a little hallway on the back wall to the right of the long service counter. A little computer desk is near the hallway's entrance.
comment:
Mangiare is a restaurant. Its Yelp page:

http://www.yelp.com/biz/0Z_0xrSi9yAA4I4fBm0T0g

name: Starbucks
directions: At the corner of Winnetka and Ventura near Ralphs.
comment: Close by 9:30pm most nights but has a good GLBTQ friendly staff. Bathrooms are to the left of the hand-off bar.

name: midstate Medical Center
directions: Emergency waiting room bathrooms are gender neutral

name: Honest Weight Food Co-Op
directions: Through Front Door, hang a left, next to the sevice desk
comment: hours are 7 am to 8 pm everday but sunday which is  9 am to 7 pm. good food too! and fun!

name: Flavour Cafe
directions: Slightly behind and to the right of the cash register.
comment: Gay-owned, queer friendly establishment with great coffee, snacks & food!  Hosts local events, exhibits local art, has free book swap and free WiFi.  All around great place!

name: Build-A-Bear Workshop
directions: To the very back of the store, behind the 'Dress Me' section.
comment: If you can stand the kiddies & families, this a great, clean place to pee in the mall that has single-stall, genderfree bathrooms.

name: Affirmations Community Center
directions: Enter on 9 mile or from parking lot in back.  Gender Inclusive Restroom is on the lower level.
comment:
Monday-Wednesday 9am-9pm

Thursday 9am-11pm

Friday-Saturday 9am-12Midnight



www.goaffirmations.org

name: Loblaws (Maple Leaf Gardens)
directions: On the ground floor, you go past the cash registers and there are 3 gender neutral, accessible washrooms.

name: Ferry Bldg
directions: Top of Market.

name: Mendel Art Gallery
directions: Top floor near the eating area. Hours 9-9 daily

name: Chapel Hill
directions: Right in, to the right.

name: Cafe Los Cuiles
directions: by the counter, kitchen area
comment: clean and nice. a cafe with decent snacks, vegetarian fare and lots of nice students!

name: Stetson's
directions: Up on the second floor of the bar the bathroom is a single stall and has both M/F icons on the door.
comment: There was a bit of a line, but the crowd there was pretty laidback for a college bar crowd.

name: Glen's Market
directions: As you walk into the store you'll be facing the end of the check out lanes. Turn left and the bathroom is in the corner on your left.
comment: Store is open 24 hours. The bathroom is single occupant genderfree. It's often rather dirty so use at your own risk ;)

name: Valero Gas Station
directions: Take the Appian Way exit off of I-80, can't miss it; it's on the corner.  Walk in the sliding doors and go left past the snacks.  There are two stalls for woman.  Pretty clean for a gas station.
comment: Great stop before reaching the city.  They're open late!

name: Grand Valley State University AuSable Hall
street: AuSable Hall, Grand Valley State University
directions: 2nd floor in corridor full of Psychology faculty offices - walk toward the window full of plants and the bathroom will be on the left
comment: The building is open weekdays from @7am-10PM

name: Triumph Brewing Company
directions: First floor, in the back, up and around the little ramp on the left.
comment: Pretty cool bathroom.  It's set up more like a dressing room than a bathroom.  You walk into a general area, then there are probably 10 self-contained stalls (toilet and sink).

name: Ray's Place
comment: Great Vietnamese restaurant in Spenard with wonderful inexpensive soup and two gender-free restrooms.

name: Dunkin Donuts
directions: Depending on which door you walk in, it's either to your right or straight and to the left. Just ask an employee if you really can't find it, they'll point it out to you.

name: Subway Sandwiches & Salads
comment: on route 140

name: Willow Canyon Outdoor
directions: rear of the bookstore.

name: Jack London Square
directions: Foot of Broadway where it meets Jack London Square, next to the parking garage and Barnes & Noble.
comment: Not sure how late it is open.

name: Woodstar
directions: From Main Street in Northampton, going away from King/Pleasant Street, it will be on the right on Masonic Street, passing by Packard's, before Bela Vegetarian restaurant.

name: Rockridge Market Hall
directions: The key is hanging on a hook near the cooler in the Bakery section of the market. The bathrooms are actually right next door to the bakery, through the door and down the hall.

name: Alameda Marketplace
directions: Entrance is off the bakery.

name: Pizzeria Paradiso
directions: One accessible genderfree locking bathroom on the first floor. Two non-accessible gendered locking bathrooms on the lower level by the bar.
comment: It's in a restaurant.

name: Barnes & Noble
directions: top floor at the top of the escalator by the cafe
comment: 2 locking gendered bathrooms

name: Central Park
directions: To the right of the basketball courts, to the left of the skatepark. Right before the baseball field, cant miss it.
comment: Great bathroom if you really need to poop. It's open to the public but rarely will anyone intrude on you as you drop the deuce. Highly recommended from an experienced user.

name: South Valley UU Society
directions: Building is locked, ring bell for access. Genderfree bathroom is in back annex. (There are gendered bathrooms in the basement.) Ask for directions.  Minister and other employees are trans.
comment: Open Sunday mornings for services, plus Monday 9-12, Tue 10-2, Wed 2-9, Thu 10 -2. Call at other times. 944-9723

name: Fuse
directions: All the bathrooms are unisex but have urinals around the corner. Also, cool reasturant

name: Truffle Pigs Cafe
directions: Enter into the store part and take a left at the desk.  2 clearly-marked gender-free washrooms.  Food there is pretty good too. JTI

name: Climb 306
comment: If you aren't there to climb, then just ask to use washroom.

name: Hunter College
directions: Second floor of the Hunter College North building, right outside OASIS office (room 217).

name: carvel
directions: rear

name: Quinsigamond Community College
directions: In the Suprenant building, between the Faculty Lounge and Faculty Offices on the first floor.  The faculty rooms are locked, so you\'ll need someone to let you in.
comment: The bathroom is technically for faculty and staff only, but if the faculty rooms are open, or if the right people are there, you can use it.  Due to too many doors, the bathroom is most likely not wheelchair accessible.

name: The Burger Ranch
directions: Bathroom is located outside. Left hand side while facing building.
comment: Bathroom (clean!) is for customers only. Very nice employees, just ask for the bathroom key once you've bought a soda or food.

name: Koffee Kat
directions: It is directly in front of you after you walk in the front door.  The people at the coffee shop are extremely nice too :)

name: LivinGood
directions: Walk in the front door and you'll see the bathrooms at the far left-hand corner of the restaurant.  No one will say anything if you just walk in.  The food is really good too :)

name: UMass Amherst - Lederle
directions: LGRT 16th floor, middle hallway on the right
comment: designated "female" but individual locking, available whenever the building is open (which is nearly 24/7).

name: Nooch
directions: In the back of the restaurant, there is a gender neutral bathroom.

name: Starbucks
street: Near sothern end of 6th Ave, between 7th and 8th Streets.
directions: In the back of the store, there are two gender neutral bathrooms.

name: Burger King
directions: Just East of I-5, exit #631  Right inside front door.
comment:
Not the cleanest, but extremely convenient for travelers on I-5

Two non sexed single occupant restrooms

name: Uncommon Grounds
directions: Back of the coffee shop.
comment: Come right in and enjoy. Typically very clean.

name: Target
directions: Straight in the front door, hang an immediate left. You're there!

name: Java Jive
street: Corner of KIldaire Farm and Lochmere Dr.
directions: JavaJive is on the left-hand side of the plaza, next to the wine shop. The bathrooms are behind a wall on the right-hand side of the store.
comment: If you're going to try and sneak in (they post "no public restrooms" signs) use the door facing Kildaire Farm Rd, because it's away from the counter and closer to the bathrooms. You'd be best off just buying something if it's not busy.

name: Seattle-Tacoma Int'l Airport
directions: Several 'family' restrooms located near regular restrooms down by the baggage claim
comment: Not all the restroom locations have a "family" restroom nearby....  but I know at least 2 are on the airport side of the room (not the street side)  So keep looking.

name: Target
directions: As soon as you walk in, the bathrooms are to your right. The first door you come up to is the family bathroom.

name: Goodberry's Ice Cream
street: Kildaire Farm Dr. and Wrenn Rd.
directions: Outdoor ice cream stand next to Hibernian Pub.
comment: Have to ask for key. It tells me whether I'm passing convincingly because of which key they hand me.

name: Lewis & Clark College
directions:
ADA general access: student center, top floor, end of the hall across from the dining hall (there are two sex-specific restrooms, and one sex-blind).



Guest access: guests of students living at the college can use nearly any residence hall restroom -- they default to gender-free/sex-blind status. Student ID or student host are needed to access residence hall restrooms, however.

name: National Hispanic Cultural Center
directions:
The building has a few bathrooms, some gender specific, and at least one that is either 'family' or just not designated.

It's on the first floor, in a hall near the theaters (not the gallery).

name: Burger King
directions: there are two single stall, gender neutral bathrooms on the side of the building closest to market
comment: i'm not sure whether you have to buy anything or not, it's a bit of a sketch location, but hey, it's gender neutral!

name: Denver international Airport
directions: In each terminal near the 'mens room' at the center hub - there is a small door simply marked 'toilet'  It is on both sides of the center hub.  The label is on a small placard - you'll miss it if you are not looking.

name: 29'th St Mall Restrooms
directions: In the main plaza across from the security  station near Borders Bookstore.
comment: Two Family restrooms of a large size.

name: All Souls Unitarian Church
directions: All 3 bathrooms are located by the main entrance. The accessible/gender neutral bathroom is closest to the door, followed my Men's and then Women's.
comment: These bathrooms are safe places.

name: Mallard's
comment: Single stall bathrooms are pink and blue but there is a little sign that says they're gender-neutral, it's a cute touch.  Great local, natural ice cream and vegan coconut ice too!

name: University of Louisville, Ekstrom Library
directions: First floor, in back of building in Tuliptree Cafe

name: Lifelong AIDS Alliance
directions:
The first door immediately down the hall at the Seneca Building, just past the front desk, ground floor.

Mapquest will lose you; come up to it from Madison and the large signs will be more of a clue.  It is the less obvious of the two Lifelong buildings on either side of the Copy Mart.
comment: There are two buildings at Lifelong and while both have bathrooms, I'm only certain of the one in the Seneca building.  The building, which is the main client-focused building, is open from 8:30 to 5:00 every day.  The staff and volunteers are all friendly and will never judge you; the volunteers are expected not to talk about anyone they work with or for.

name: Middlebush Hall Ground Floor
directions: Middlebush Hall is located on the University of Missouri campus, at the corner of 9th Street and University Avenue.  Parking is metered.  Bathroom is on the ground floor.
comment: Typically, the building is unlocked whenever students are around.  You might have trouble getting there on Sundays, holidays, or in the middle of the night.

name: Mama Buzz Cafe
directions: walk right in the door, you'll see a mural which is also the bathroom door!

name: Cafe Colucci
directions: behind the dining area
comment: great Ethiopian food!

name: Bay Cove Human Services
directions: 5th floor, take elevator up then turn left
comment: human services agency where people generally are only there with an appointment, but you shouldn't run into trouble since people also go there to apply for jobs and do trainings and things. it also seems big enough that everyone would just assume you're there for another department.

name: ten stone
directions: go past the bar and back on the left, in the direction of 21st street. you can go either way around the bar.
comment: good beer, the people are a little uptight but the bathroom's gender free and great in a pinch

name: brew ha ha
directions: straight through to the back, two gender free stalls.

name: Gilmore Skytrain Station - Taco Del Mar
directions: Across the street from the Gilmore Skytrain Station, fast food place beside Starbucks called Taco Del Mar (inside and on the right). Two washrooms: one labeled female (locked for employees) and the other labeled male/female/accessible (unlocked when I was there).

name: Caffeine Cafe
directions: Straight to the back and hang a left, two gender neutral, single occupancy bathrooms await!
comment: We're Trans owned and host a couple Trans events.

name: Triangle Town Center
street: Corner of Capital Blvd and Old Wake Forest Rd. Near 540
directions: 2nd floor, upstairs from the food court, just behind the elevators.  There are 2 of them each with an adult toilet, a childs toilet, and a changing table.
comment: Always clean!

name: Quail Ridge Books
directions: back corner

name: Frites Alors!
street: ave du parc, east side just north of fairmont
directions: at back of building on the left
comment: genderfree washroom at back of store - if vusy, walk thru and act like you're looking for someone, if not you could still probably confidently walk right in

name: Target
directions: Just inside the entrance to the left before you get to the customer service desk.
comment:
Single stall "family" restroom.



M-Sa: 8:00 a.m.-10:00 p.m.

Su: 8:00 a.m.-9:00 p.m.

name: The Potter's Rib
directions: If you face the counter, it is at the end of the hallway you see on the right.
comment:
11am-7:30pm Tuesday through Saturday



Also try the food. It's homemade barbeque and whatnot.

name: SeaTac Airport
directions: At least the S-gates have 'family' bathrooms flagged as gender-free. There may be more in other terminals.
comment: This is an airport, so there is a lot of traffic around. The 'family' bathrooms are located on either end of the terminal satellite, between the entrances for the gendered bathrooms and easy to overlook.

name: Seattle/Tacoma International Airport

When you're hanging out and/or ordering, sometimes they are really accepting and chill while sometimes they are caught off guard and confused if you don't look like a binary-genetic girl or boy.  I've never had an issue with the bathroom though.  The bathroom is closer to the entrance than where most of the employees stand, so you might be able to sneak in without paying, but it's difficult.

Just stroll on in and do your business... you are not at all likely to be noticed, especially if you are college-aged or professor-aged.

name: Georgia State University - Kell Hall
directions: This is on the first floor of Kell Hall, near the Peachtree Center Ave entrance, just before the elevators. ------- As of July 2011, if you enter the building from the Peachtree Center Ave entrance, there will be a large open space eventually connecting to Sparks Hall in front of you; a very large sign for and small hallway to the Cooperative Learning Lab to your right; and a short hallway leading to the elevators to your left. ------- Turn left and walk a few yards - there will be a small alcove with a women's restroom and this single-occupancy, accessible, non-gender-specific bathroom.
comment: __Locking the door:__ It may not be immediately clear, but the door to this bathroom *does* lock. It does not have a physical latch, but in the corner across from the toilet (diagonal from the sink) there are two buttons at about three feet above the floor. One locks the door and the other unlocks and automatically opens the door. ------- __Accessibility button by the door:__ This button to automatically open the door does not work. The buttons in the corner described above function fine. ------- __Hours:__ GSU is open late - especially this building, which tends to host a lot of astronomy labs. This building will probably be locked very late at night and very early in the morning, and may have somewhat more limited hours during the summer. ------- __More info about this building:__ The official university webpage for Kell Hall is at  http://www.gsu.edu/site2005/29529.html  or  tinyurl.com/gsukell . ------- __User-Safety:__ Our school is very racially diverse, so campus security is not likely to harass users of this bathroom who are not GSU students *solely* on the basis of their ethnicity, but the police at GSU and in downtown Atlanta in general have been 'cracking down on homelessness' (i.e., perpetuating racism and classism like it'll fix the economic and structural problems in the city), so you may get flack or worse if you 'look' very poor, especially if you are older than traditional college student age and not white.
