comment: All Potbelly locations are now gender neutral

name: Burgerville
directions: Just go back and to the left for two genderfree single-stall bathrooms.
comment: There wasn\'t a sign for this Burgerville on the freeway, but it\'s just a couple minutes off I-5. Good food, decent veg options

name: Nordstrom - Ala Moana
directions: Single stall, locking \"family\" restrooms on the 1st and 3rd floor.
comment: Unlike \"family\" restrooms in the main part of the mall, Nordstrom\'s restrooms are usually available.

name: Sunmoon Urgent Care
directions: It\'s inside the door to the rest of the clinic.
comment: If you\'re a patient there, you can definitely use the bathroom. I don\'t know if they\'d let you use it if you\'re not a patient. You can always claim to be one  of Dr. Xia Li\'s patients since they get such high turnover. (213) 484-1289

name: IOTA Club and Cafe
directions: Ground floor restaurant and bar. There are gender neutral, handicapped accessible bathrooms. No stairs in any public areas.
comment: Great music from nationally touring bands in the evening. See their web site for menu, hours, and events at www.iotaclubandcafe.com

name: Locals Only Art and Music Pub
directions: Gendered, single occupancy men\'s room that locks. Gendered, three-stall women\'s room.
comment: Great pub with a wide beer selection, indie bands on weekends, open mike or blues jam, poetry night, experimental, electronica, jazz and improv night. See their web site at www.localsonlyindy.com.

name: Walla Walla Bread Co.
directions: near the tables and chairs towards the back of the building
comment:
Tuesday-Friday 7-5

Saturday 7-3

name: Colville St. Patisserie
directions: to the right of the counter/cashier area
comment:
M-Th 9AM-8PM

F-S 9AM-10PM

Sun 9AM-5PM

name: Trader Joe\'s
directions: Straight back past the cashiers. Two unisex singles.

name: University of Buffalo Law Library
directions: Go into O\\\'Brian Hall (the law school) and go up to the second floor to enter the law library. If you come across a cafe, you have gone the wrong direction, turn around and head the opposite way. Go to the back of the library and turn right to find the elevator.  Take the elevator up to any floor and find a gender neutral single stall locking restroom to your left immediatly after stepping out of the elevator.
comment: The restrooms can only be used during library hours, check here for those http://law.lib.buffalo.edu/about/hours-location.asp Driving directions to O\\\'Brian available at the link as well.

name: Best Western Grand Manor Inn
directions: In the Rose Room (breakfast room), next to the window

name: Gateway Movie Theater
directions: Across from theater 8

name: Cup A Joe
directions: Next to the Chelsea Theater.

name: The Coffee Bean and Tea Leaf
directions: On your left down the hall when you enter. You can see the doors from the sidewalk through the big windows.

name: Kmart
directions: It\'s way in the back, but often deserted.

name: Jamila\'s Mediterranean Tunisian Cafe
directions: Walk in the door and head down the hall. Its on the right hand side right past the restaurant.

name: Mojo Coffee House
directions: Enter the coffee shop and exit the back door. Go back a ways (almost to the end of the building. Its on the right hand side.
comment: Open till midnight. You might want to buy a coffee or something after you use the restroom.

name: Teavolve
directions: al the way toward the back and turn left.

name: Starbucks
directions: All the way at the back.
comment: Two individual locking rooms, spacious, non-gendered.

name: Rainbow Cafe
directions: At the end of a little alley off King\'s Parade.  Restaurant is downstairs, toilet is on the ground floor, straight across from the entrance
comment: Closed on Sunday evenings and all Monday

name: Harold\'s Laundry
directions: In the back on the left.
comment: Open 24 hours!

name: La Costa Coffee Roasting
directions: It is in the back by the water cooler. Employees can\'t see you go in if you go through the side door that is open next to the water cooler.
comment: A good place to go if you don\'t want to go to the bathroom at the movie theater.

name: Trader Joe\'s
directions: It is in the very back in the storage area. You can ask an employee where it is.
comment: They have really good food there and free samples.

name: Jamba Juice
directions: Ask an employee for the key.
comment: I\'ve never used this restroom without being there to buy something. Buying a smoothie or chips or something would probably be best.

name: Me Bar/Sky Bar
directions: top floor!
comment: rooftop bar at the la quinta inn.  awesome bar - single locking non gendered bathroom.

name: McFoster\'s Natural Kind Cafe
directions: Two restrooms, one on either side by the entrance. This is a very lgbt-friendly cafe!
comment: Amazing food, laid back staff, lgbt film screenings... What more could you want? I love this place!

name: 24 Diner
directions: At the back of the restaurant.

name: UNC campus- Venable Hall
directions: It\'s on the ground level next to the women\'s rest room.  take a right and another right out of the elevator.
comment: Sometimes the door is locked all day.  I\'m not sure why.

name: Jimbo\'s
directions: It is on the left side of the smoothie/juice bar.

name: Croutons
directions: In the very back by the soda fountain.

name: Loblaws
directions: At the front of the store, after the cashes.

name: Ahora Mexican Restaurant
directions: Downstairs off the street.

name: Jock Turcott University Centre
directions: On the bottom floor near the access to the pedestrian mall - near the Foot Patrol and Community Protection offices.

name: Java Madness
directions: Enter the front door, take the right before the counter. Door is on the left.
comment: 6am to 6pm, possibly longer on weekends, possibly shorter in the winter. Building is accessible, but hall to bathroom might be too tight for some.

name: North Central College - Goldspohn Hall
directions: Second Floor
comment: Open until 10:30

name: Sea Isle City, NJ
directions: On boardwalk just off the beach

name: Valley View Mall
directions: Near the bathrooms by the food court. It\'s just across from the gendered bathrooms.
comment: Clean, gender-neutral, and nice! Saved my butt the other day.

name: Papalecco
comment: I\'ve only gone here when I wanted to buy something so I\'m not completely sure you have to. The staff are really friendly. They have great gelato and coffee here (the only things I\'ve had here).

name: Starbucks
comment: This is located in the Lumberyard next to St. Tropez Restaurant.

name: Taste Coffee House
directions: in the back, to the right

name: Brooks Hall, University of Georgia, North Campus
directions: From the south entrance of the building (closest to Sanford Hall, farthest from Caldwell Hall), walk straight in. It is to the right of the double doors to the stairwell.
comment: Available whenever the building is open.

name: Sugartown Vintage Boutique
comment:
Single-stall /locking gender free bathroom



This bathroom listing provided by shop owner :)

name: Bella Pizzeria
directions: Back through the hallway next to the register

name: Starbucks
directions: 1st floor in the back.  Walk to the stairs and turn.
comment: The staff is incredibly queer and queer-friendly.

name: Van Pelt-Dietrich Library Center
directions: Many floors have single-stall and/or locking restrooms which are gender nonspecific.
comment: A valid University of Pennsylvania ID, state ID, or driver\'s license is needed to gain access to the building.

name: Agnes Scott College
directions: In the campus center and library there are assorted gender neutral bathrooms.  Campus center requires student/staff id after 8pm.
comment: Library is the best bet.

name: Vassar College
directions:
Library Basement (Open to public)



All Dorms (need to be a student)



Most academic buildings have at least 1

name: Horseshoe Casino
directions: One to the right of Total Rewards desk, another to the rear of the casino left of the cage and bar.
comment: Must be 21 to enter casino

name: Metro Grocery Store
directions: It is a single use, family room.  Once you enter the front door, go strait down the row of checkouts and past the flower stands.  Between the flowers and the refrigerator full of orange juice is a small hallway.  It is the first room in this hall, and should be visible right away when you reach the hall.
comment: As this is a 24 hour super market, it is pretty easy to get in late at night.

name: Galaxy cinema
directions: In the hall to the theaters, there is a gender neutral family room.
comment: Will need to have a ticket to get in (ie, already there to watch a movie)

name: Ideya
directions: Just go straight from the front door and take a right when you get past the bar. There are two different bathrooms, both with unmarked doors.
comment: Open seven days a week. The food, a blend of Latin and South American, is absolutely incredible, and the posters don\'t lie when they advertise the best mojitos in New York - I recommend stopping in for a meal if you can! Casual-to-classy dress. The staff\'s pretty chill if you just need the restroom, though.

name: Scarborough Town Centre
directions: Lower floor near the food court has locking private washrooms  There are a few others scattered around.

name: Richard Roberts Building
directions: Turn left as you go in, behind the auditorium.
comment: Look like a student.

name: Ossining Public Library
directions: First floor, on the back wall, to the left of the circulation desk.
comment: Hours: Mon.-Thurs. 9-9; Fri.-Sat. 9-5:30; Sun. 12-5.

name: Paper Chase Cafe & Newsstand
directions: In the front door and up the stairs.  Turn to your right and up another small set of stairs.  Bathrooms are on the right.  There are two separate, single stall bathrooms with locking doors.
comment:
Awesome food with lots of menu choices.  Great staff.  Great atmosphere. Love the layout.



After eating there with my kids one night, I thanked them for having non-gendered washrooms that were safe and accessible. Without skipping a beat, the person working the counter said Thanks for noticing. We want everyone to feel safe & comfortable here.

name: Soul Full Cup
directions: Past the counter and on your right.
comment: Tiny bathroom, might not be handicap accessible.

name: Heavenly Cup
directions: If you enter from the front of the building (near the counter), go right, towards the stairs, into the little nook and it\'s on your left. If you go through the side door, facing the counter but on the opposite side of the room, it\'s in the nook to your right, also facing you.
comment: A little isolated, but the employees are usually cool, the coffee is excellent, and the genderfree bathroom is big.

name: Chautauqua Lake Rest Area
directions: Between the traditionally gendered restrooms - men\'s on the right, women\'s on the left. It\'s unisex/family.
comment: One of the cleanest rest stops around.

name: The Forest
directions: Accessible toilet is in the main cafe, other genderfree toilets downstairs in the basement.
comment: Forest is a wacky awesome place, run by volunteers and spontaneously exploding with creativity here and there. Don\'t be surprised if these aren\'t the cleanest toilets ever though!

name: UNO Milo Bail Student Center
directions: Come in through the Dodge St. entrance (the shuttle bus pick-up). Take an immediate left and left again; there are two gender-neutral bathrooms next to the computer lab.
comment: If you enter the building and just go straight, then enter the first door, you\'ll find the Women\'s Resource Center and Agency of Gender and Sexual Orientation. WRC has free feminine products and GSO can provide a list of all gender-neutral bathrooms on campus.

name: Willard Straight Hall
directions: South side of the building, right next to the women\'s restroom. Single stall and locks, very brightly lit inside
comment: There\'s a full-length mirror right next to the toilet, so look away if you don\'t like seeing your face while doing business!

name: Chandler House
directions: All the toilets are gender neutral!
comment: It\'s a UCL building, so only accessible to those with a UCL student card, but if you\'ve got any University of London ID you may be able to pretend you want a book from their library.

name: Tallahassee Community College
directions: On the first floor of the Academic Computing Center

name: Disneyland
directions: There is a family bathroom that is between the end of Main St. on the left side, before you get to the castle, and Frontierland. It\'s right by the pathway you could use to head back to Rancho del Zocalo. It\'s a tan door & building with a triangle shaped sign on it (triangle inside a circle).
comment: Once you are in the park, the restroom is free. It is a single occupancy, non-gendered facility.

name: Carleton University
directions: University Center 3rd and 4th floor.

name: Walmart
directions: Single-stall family restroom is located at the back of the store.
comment: This is a gender-neutral, accessible, family restroom. All genders/ages/etc. may use this single-stall restroom.

name: West Oaks Mall
directions: Right by the bathrooms near the food court.

name: Dunn Bros. Coffee
directions: In the back of the building, not visible from the front of the store.
comment: You need a key to get into the bathroom, but it\'s easy to snag one if you pretend you know what you\'re doing and don\'t try to get one as soon as you come into the store.

name: Juliette restaurant
directions: towards the back; ask the waitstaff.
comment: This bar/restaurant has an amazing francophile aesthetic; it\'s furnished with a million antique objects from France. True to the last detail, there\'s even a \"Mixte\" single-stall bathroom as well as single-stalls for the women\'s & men\'s rooms.  Beautiful!  Classy! Gender-neutral!  yay!

name: the Autonomous Centre of Edinburgh
directions: The toilet is out the back. Also has baby changing facilities/ They aren\\\'t open all the time: every saturday 12-6pm, other times listed on their website.
comment: they are a meeting space, believe in mutual aid, they have a food co-op library bookstore as well as selling products supporting campaigns such as Free West Papua and the Zapatista movement

name: H-E-B
directions: North-East part of the building. Enter the building and take a left. Family restroom is single occupancy.

name: Revolutionary Grounds
directions: Just walk in. It\'s a cute, small little place.
comment: Queer & trans-friendly.

name: John\'s Lunch
directions:
Its a pretty small place and the bathrooms are in the back.  Follow the path through the tables and the counter to the back.  Turn to  your left or you\'ll walk.  Door is on the left.  Unmarked but usually left standing open. There\'s only one way so you can\'t go wrong!



Everyone is friendly so if you\'re unsure, just ask a customer or staff member and they\'ll direct you. 



Its also very busy and super popular so there is almost always a crowd at the front door. Just make y our way through.  Usually everyone moves for you anyways.  



Definitely NOT accessible.
comment:
http://www.johnslunch.com/



People come from all over to have fish or clams and chips at John\'s.  If you have the time take 1/2 hour to have a great lunch for pretty cheap.

name: Cimarron Books and Coffee
directions: Go in the front door and head for the left end of the coffee counter. This corner is full of Music and t-shirts. Open the door that is covered in pictures. This is the Bathroom.
comment: Good coffee, Fun to hang out in as long as the owner isn't there (She's just not as much fun) Good coffee (Again as long as the owner isn't the one making the coffee) A good place for political activism / Anti-bush type stuff. Lots of fun local area books. And a wonderful Cat named Willa Cather and yes she is allowed to go out.

name: St. Louis Bubble Tea
directions: Locked, key given out to customers.

name: The Grind Cafe
directions: Bathroom is in the hallway going towards the back entrance.
comment: Really good food and coffee.  Sponsors musical events upstairs.  Welcoming environment.

name: Renaissance hotel
directions: Second floor of hotel, no room key needed. Top of escalator, turn right then left past the elevators.

name: Grand Central Mall

comment: There are two non-gendered single occupancy locking bathrooms.  They are open Mon-Thu 11am-11pm; Fri-Sat 11am-12am; Sun 11am-10pm.

comment: The building\'s open when classes are in session (most of the day during the school year).

name: Biblocafe

name: The Park Bench Cafe
directions: Inside the restaurant, down the short (well, it follows, unless the building was constructed operating on the same principle as a Tardis) hallway.
comment: It should be noted that there are public restrooms in the park behind this place, but that to my knowledge they are not a single stall nor genderfree. They are, however, likely to be relatively unpeopled.

directions: In the back, to the left, next to the drinking fountain there is a genderless, single bathroom with a locking door.
comment: 10am to around 5pm on weekdays. 9am to 4pm on Saturdays. Closed on Sundays. Summer hours are slightly different, but still closed on Sundays. They have a website with more information. Just search for the library's name.

name: The Smiling Goat
directions: Street level access.
comment:
Monday to Friday 8am - 7pm

Saturday 9am - 6pm

Sunday 10am - 5pm



One single-stall washroom located to the right of the counter.



The Smiling Goat is an organic espresso bar. Located near the corner of Spring Garden & South Park, it is a nice cozy spot for a great cup of coffee (or apple chai-der). They also have a selection of baked goods, including Great Canadian Bagels, plus free wifi (just ask for the password).

Open Mon-Sat 7:30am-6pm; Sun 8am-6pm.

Known for great coffee and breakfast items. Small patio for days when the sun is shining.

Free wifi (limited electricity plugs, so aim for a window seat if your battery is running low).

comment:
Mandolin Cafe bathroom is especially nice for pooping. Blow it up to your heart's delight.



Large private bathroom with high powered jet flush toilet and usually stocked with an ample supply of air freshener makes for an especially pleasing pooping experience.  There is also an air powered hand dryer for your amusement. Enjoy!

name: McMaster University Math Building

comment: Very queer friendly space. The doors have snails on them, one of them peeing standing up, one of them peeing sitting down, just to show the facilities inside.

comment: Nice place and good food!

comment: It used to be the womens bathroom, but the mens room is so aweful men were using it. When they built the new womens room, they just let that one be for everyone.  So now there is a mens room (don't go there!), a womens room and a gender neutral room.

name: Chocolate Shoppe Ice Cream

comment: You need a key, but just ask!

name: Collins LLC

Walk in the main doors of Edmonson Hall from the stone veranda; door will be directly on left. 



Another gender-neutral restroom is located on the ground floor through the door that exits to the south of Edmonson Hall.
comment: ID is only required after 8 p.m. on weekdays and all day on weekends, but if you ask for the restroom someone will definitely let you inside.

name: Clemson University, Jordan Hall

There are staircases at either end of the building and an elevator inside.  If you're coming from the south end, go past the DNA Learning Center and take the first left.  From the north end, just go down the hall and take the second left.  There's a single stall unisex wheelchair-accessible bathroom across the hall from the gendered bathrooms.
comment: Jordan locks in the evening, sometime after 6:30 pm.  There's always random people in the Learning Center, and the part of the hall where the bathrooms are is usually empty, so don't worry about people noticing you.

name: Carnation Building
directions: Bottom floor off the main atrium
comment: 8am 5pm  Mon-Fri for sure - other times spotty

just enter building go to your right both male and female bath rooms are single use locking doors and kept clean.

pay cash for fuel as the pay at the pump charges a penalty for there use.

name: Seomra Spraoi

Go down the street until you see a black door with 'Seomra Spraoi' in pink.
comment: Seomra Spraoi is open Monday-Friday 6pm-10pm. It is an activist social centre. While it has accessibility issues, all of its bathrooms are gender free. It is a free social space so no buying of anything is required!

The first road parallel to Parliament St on the west side is Exchange Street Upper. At the bottom of it, in the corner, is The Exchange Dublin
comment: The Exchange Dublin is a free, grassroots-run arts space in central Dublin. It's meant to be a non-commercial space for people to socialise and for arts and activist projects to be hosted. The place is open from 11am to 11pm every day. Its only bathroom is gender free, and one is not required to purchase anything to use it.

name: Crisis Intervention Services
directions: Located in the United Way building across the street from Hy-Vee. There are several disabled parking spots located directly across from the main entrance by the lot on the east side of the building (towards Hy-Vee). You enter through 2 outer pull handle doors and there are no steps. Go to the far right corner of the main room when you enter, and go down the hall to the 2nd door on your left (Crisis Intervention Services office). Go through the waiting room and keep going straight toward the back door. The public restroom is on the left just past the kitchen area. Parking is also available along the north side of the building and you can enter through the back door (lever handle), after climbing 1 step. The public restroom is on your right as soon as you come in the back door.
comment: Office hours are 8:30-5 Monday-Friday. You can come in through the back door, but they prefer you use the main entrance. Please ring the bell in the waiting room or otherwise get an employee's attention and tell them you just need to use the public restroom. They're allies and shouldn't give you a hard time; they just need to know who's on the premises at all times and why, since they provide confidential services. The restroom would not meet ADA standards, but it's more accessible than standard bathroom stalls. The toilet seat is standard height but there's a plastic "booster" seat you can take on and off. It's a single toilet room with urinal and sink, with a door that locks. (Turn knob, and you have to push in and turn to lock it.) They have posted that PAS/help is available by staff (usually all female)upon request.

name: Police Department- ASUPD- Arizona State University

name: Business Administration A Building- BA- Arizona State University
directions: Take the elevators to the second floor. Go right down hallway. Should be on right.

name: Business Administration C Building- BAC- Arizona State University
directions: Use doors nearest Starbucks to enter building. Restrooms should be on right; elevators should be on left.

name: College of Design North- CDN - Arizona State University
street: Design North 810 S. Forest Mall. Tempe, AZ 85287
directions: Enter from south entrance. Turn left to take stairs to the second floor. Restrooms should be on left, very near by.

name: Center for Family Studies- CFS- Arizona State University
directions: Should be easier to access from ‰ÛÏgraduate student‰Û entrance doors. A majority of the building seems to be gated, around a large playground. Graduate student entrance doors are on west side of building. Anyway, enter there. Take stairs up. Should be two gender neutral restrooms.

name: Campus Children\'s Center- CHILD- Arizona State University
directions: Must have business there in order to use their restrooms. There are two, if you go down the hallway to your right.

name: Chuparosa Hall- CHUPA - Arizona State University
directions: Chuparosa also goes by the name ‰ÛÏbuilding D‰Û of Hassayampa. Come from the east, to access room D101, the lobby. Restroom is located a little bit in, and to the right, from lobby entrance. Only open during lobby hours. Seemed a little bit restrictive.

name: Lattie F. Coor Hall- COOR- Arizona State University
directions: One on every floor. On first floor, located between main computing commons area (north) and gender specific (women‰Ûªs) restrooms (south, and along a west wall). If taking elevator up to other floors, go toward main building entrance doors, and they should be on your left, on the west side. Highly recommended due to the fact that there are many, and if one is full, just take an elevator up to get to another. However, the first floor one is not recommended so much. Sometimes the lock does not work, but usually when that happens there is a sign that says so. In any case, double check if you‰Ûªd like.

name: Cowden Family Resources- COWDN- Arizona State University
directions: When coming from west entrance doors, go straight down hallway. Look to right. However, when taking more ‰ÛÏmain‰Û front entrance doors from east side, at first fork turn right. At next fork, left. Look to left for restroom.

name: Engineering Center G Wing- ECG - Arizona State University
directions: Located on third floor of building, directly behind elevators.

name: Payne Hall- EDB- Arizona State University
directions: Use Payne Hall East, not Payne Hall West. Might be better to enter Payne Hall East through the outdoors corridor that links buildings ED and EDB together, because restrooms are nearer to that entrance, instead of the east entrance. Anyway, take stairs to basement. Gender neutral restroom should be near gender specific (women‰Ûªs) restroom. A second gender neutral restroom is currently being built in Payne West.

name: Nelson Fine Art Center - FAC- Arizona State University
directions: Enter from east entrance that is slightly underground; you will need to take slight stairs to get here. You will arrive on the ‰ÛÏL‰Û floor. Follow hallway a little bit in. Gender neutral restroom should be right next to gender specific (women‰Ûªs) restroom; both are sort of tucked in a pocket in the wall. Building is very rounded and dark, and kind of secluded.

name: Gammage Auditorium- GGMA- Arizona State University
directions: Enter through main entrance. Turn left. Go through doors. Go a little bit down a hallway. On left should be restroom. Unsure if this restroom is open to the public; only ever been personally used during a show to Gammage.

name: Health Service Building- HSB- Arizona State University
directions: Enter through main entrance, located on south side of building. Pass reception desk, by turning left. Turn right. Continue down hall until there is a major hall on left. Turn there. Take hall, and when available turn left, where gender neutral restroom should be. There is at least one other gender neutral restroom, but staff mentioned it was for patients, so check in is likely needed for that one, and is likely deeper/more secluded in the building.

name: Physical Education East- PEBE- Arizona State University
directions: Building may be entered from either the north side or south side. When entering from north side, turn left, once immediately able. Continue down hallway, and pass couch chairs, to just about the end, where gender neutral restroom is.

name: Interdisciplinary A- INTDS A - Arizona State University
directions: When entering from east, keep going straight (west). Turn right. Go to end of hallway. On left should be a corner full of restrooms. Gender neutral bathroom is left-most in the corner of restrooms. Recommended, if seclusion is desired, due to lack of traffic through building.

name: Interdisciplinary Science and Technology Building I - ISTB 1- Arizona State University
directions: Enter from south-east corner of building. Gender neutral restroom should be just behind main lobby desk, on right side. Possibly requires Sun Card, since it is behind a lobby desk.

name: Interdisciplinary Sciences and Technology Building V- ISTB 5- Arizona State University
directions: Enter from west side of building. Continue down a hall, keeping along the right as much as possible. Turn right. Gender neutral restroom should be near a water fountain. A little bit hard to access, as it seems very tucked into the building.

name: Juniper Hall Barrett Campus- JNHAL- Arizona State University
directions: There are two. One is on the southmost corner of the building, near the fence that leads to Rural Road. To access the other, take the stairs that are located between JNHAL and RWHAL to the second floor. After exiting the elevator, turn right. There should be a fork; on the left, is a glass door. Don‰Ûªt take the glass door because it requires a Sun Card. Turn right, and go down hall to outdoors area. Gender neutral restroom should be on your left side. Because Juniper is in Barrett, access may be more restricted to it, during evening/night hours, as the building becomes locked to those without Barrett residential Sun Cards. If this happens, try to wait for someone to leave Barrett and follow in after them; residents come/go often.

name: Ross Blakley Law Library- LAWLB- Arizona State University
directions: In the center of the building, a gender neutral restroom is currently being built. The building is sort of rounded.

name: G. Homer Durham Language and Literature- LL- Arizona State University
directions: When entering from west entrance, go straight. At first major fork, turn left. Down the hall, the gender neutral restrooms should be to your right. There should be two. They are kind of not recommended, if you prefer privacy. They have very sunny, bright windows that give the illusion of lack of privacy. The LL also has a north entrance and east entrance.

name: Life Sciences Building- LSA- Arizona State University
directions: When entering from west side entrance, should be to your right, very near the entrance. Not recommended, because the lock currently does not work and the door stays open for a very long timeâÛÓit swings all the way open and refuses to swing back closed until like five whole seconds have passed, so temporary lack of privacy may pose an issue for some. Building may also be accessed from the north side and east side.

name: Life Sciences Building- LSE- Arizona State University
directions: Building may be accessed from the north-east or south-east. Gender neutral restroom is located between gender specific (women‰Ûªs‰ÛÓnorth) and gender specific (men‰Ûªs‰ÛÓsouth) restrooms. Recommended, but not. Restroom is generally good to use; however, sometimes it lacks privacy, as students often congregate outside of it, while waiting for Life Science building classes to begin. This building also has gender neutral restrooms on its S and B floors, on the south-most side. (There are three sets of doors to choose from‰ÛÓchoose the south-most one every time.) Those restrooms are also good, but again, sometimes lack privacy, especially when lab times have heavy traffic, as students will wait outside of them.

name: McClintock Hall- MCL- Arizona State University
directions: Only available to McClintock residents. When entering from main entrance (on east side), pass check in desk. Exit doors, and go into courtyard-like area. Enter a building on your immediate left (should be right across from Gammage Hall). It‰Ûªs like a microwave/rec area. Gender neutral restrooms should be on left, in that building.

name: Memorial Union- MU- Arizona State University
directions: Located on raised stair platform area across from Einstein‰Ûªs Bagels, nearest to north entrance doors. Located behind Freshens Frozen Yogurt. Recommended because the MU has a large block of business hours.

name: Murdock Hall- MUR- Arizona State University
directions: Located in room 108T1 on landing between basement and first floor. Lock does not work.

name: Noble Science Library- NOBLE- Arizona State University
directions: Enter building from north side. Keep going straight, as if you were going to the elevators. Just before the elevators, turn right. Gender neutral restroom should be on your right, between door and water fountains. Recommended.

name: Off Campus Student Services- OCSS- Arizona State University
directions: Enter building from north-west side. Must show Sun Card to check in desk. Once checked in, turn right. Should be in a student rec area. Turn left and go slightly down hall. Gender neutral restroom should be on your right. Recommended, but not. It‰Ûªs kind of hard to get to the OCSS because it is located somewhat off-campus and you must cross two roads (if coming from the west). Recommended, though, because OCSS often gives things out for free and allows ten pages of printing for free, per day, per student.

name: San Pablo Hall- PABLO- Arizona State University
directions: Requires Sun Card. Pass the front desk. Go around corner. Has two entrances.

name: Seattle Mobile Espresso
comment: Open 6am-6pm weekdays, 7:30am-6pm Saturday, 7:30am-5:30pm Sundays. Friendly staff!

name: Physical Sciences Center- PSC- Arizona State University
directions: Located in the main hall that connects Physical Sciences A, B, C, and D together, but gender neutral restroom is specifically located between halls C and D.

comment:
I\'m not qualified to say whether the bathrooms are definitely accessible or not, but for folks who need to pee and have some mobility issues that make stairs difficult, you can also access the upstairs via the ramp that connects to the porch on the back side of the bar.



Also, I didn\'t notice that they checked ID during the day, but they do at night! You will probably need to be at least 21 (definitely at least 18) to get in.



The upstairs is open from 5p-midnight Thursday through Saturday, and from 5-11p on Sunday, though they just opened and the website says these hours may be subject to change. 



General hours: they\'re closed Mondays, open noon-11p on Tuesdays, Wednesdays, and Sundays, and open noon-midnight on Thursdays, Fridays, and Saturdays.

The building is generally open during school hours (between 8a and 9p on weekdays, during the school year) for sure, I can\'t speak for other times. 



Pretty much as long as somebody figures you\'re a student and/or staff member, or a member of the community who has come to see a show at the Black Box theatre (whether you are or not) you should be just fine.

name: McCarthy Hall, Georgetown University
directions: Third floor, Justice and Diversity in Action Living and Learning Community. There are four multi-stall bathrooms (with showers) on the floor; usually two are women\'s, one is men\'s, and one is gender neutral. The specific designations for each bathroom change each academic year. Ask a student who lives on the floor, or look at the signage. The one missing a gendered sign is the gender-neutral bathroom.

name: Sahara Cafe
directions: To the left of the counter

name: Moroccan Oasis Cafe
directions: Go down the hall to the right of the front door, then turn left. The restrooms should be on your left

name: Hookah Haze

comment: This is off of Spring Forest Rd and near Capital, by the Carmike movie theater

name: Washington Square Mall
directions: Look for \'family bathrooms\' -- one is located by JCPenny, and there is one other I believe. Food court bathrooms are NOT genderfree.
comment: Open while the mall is open. There is probably still a bit of taboo with using these if you don\'t have kids in tow (they have a neat kid-friendly toilet too) but I had no problems even when I came out to find a huge family waiting.

name: The Pinhook
directions: 1st floor. Around the corner on your left.
comment: Awesome queer & transfriendly establishment!

name: DePaul University Ray Meyer Fitness Center
directions: Head down the hallway to the left as soon as you walk through the door (that would be as you\'re facing the check-in desk). The bathroom is on the right. It is a locking/one-stall bathroom, but the sign specifically says unisex.
comment: The fitness center is for DePaul faculty and students only, so unless you look like a college student, try to get in and out as quickly as you\'re able to avoid any scolding from the deskies.

name: LimeWharf
directions: In the main warehouse, ground floor, 4 toilets, 2 disabled, 2 unisex
comment: 10am-5pm, Monday to Friday, as standard, ad hoc evening and weekend events.

name: Dickinson College
directions: Anywhere on campus and in the dorms

name: Subculture Coffee
directions: Two single stall accessible restrooms, located in the back to the left of the coffee bar, behind the roasting area.
comment: Customers only, but if you're just there to hang out you should be fine.

name: 11-Jul
directions: In the back of the store

name: Jewel Grocery
directions: Past cash registers in front of store

name: Burlington Public Library
directions: There\'s a family bathroom right near the children\'s section.  It\'s inside the main doors and to the left.
comment: Super friendly library! They are open 11a-8p Monday through Thursday, and 11a-5p Friday and Saturday.

name: Silver Cup Coffee
directions: You have to ask for the key at the coffee shop, and then wade through people in business suits to get to the bathroom on the first floor, just past the mail room.
comment: The people at the coffee shop were really nice!

name: Calico Cat
directions: Directly to the back left as you walk in the door.
comment: Thrift store hours 10-5

name: Pita Pit
directions: On the main floor, past the counter
comment: The employees at this location have been spoken to about allowing anyone who comes in to use whichever bathroom they want to.

name: AUSA Student Union Building
directions: On the first floor. Go past reception, up two flights of stairs and take the corridor to the right.
comment: Clean and quiet, but tucked away and difficult to find. A student union building, but welcoming to anyone. Open during term time until late.

name: Aberdeen University Library
directions: Big glass building at the end of a paved piazza. Toilets are to the right of the building, before security desks, and on every floor above.
comment: 2 individual non-gendered toilets on each floor by the lifts, as well as an accessible toilet at either side of the building. Usually open until at least 8pm.

name: King\'s Museum
directions: Small museum, easy to find at the back. Also has baby changing facilities.
comment: Usually open until 4. Very friendly. Free. http://www.abdn.ac.uk/museums/exhibitions/kings-museum.php

name: Downtown Ace Hardware
directions: along back wall next to the exit and past the registers.
comment:
Extremely Nice!            Mon-Fri: 8:00am-8:00pm

Sat:8:00am-6:00pm 

Sun:9:00am-6:00pm

name: Jamba Juice
directions: Single-toilet restroom available for customers.  Should be obvious when you enter; just look to your left!

name: Trader Joe\'s
directions: Two single-toilet, gender-neutral restrooms are available on the left (north) side of the store, next to the wine section.

name: Madd
directions: Past the bar area and to your left.
comment: This place itself is amazing in general- I\'d advise you stick around and hang out too. It\'s gamer heaven and the staff are epic :P (open 12pm to midnight)

name: Memorial Student Center
directions: Second floor across from the ballroom (room 2300). Hidden between the men\'s and women\'s bathrooms.
comment: Clean, has music, and on the down-low so not that many people know of it.

name: Krispy Kreme
directions: To the right of the counter in the hall

name: Five Guys
directions: In the hall to the left of the counter
comment: Hours 11am-10pm every day

name: Cain Hall
directions: Second and third floor in the C wing in the middle of the hallway.
comment: They are unisex bathrooms that are very very roomy.

name: Party at Display and Costume
directions: On your right as you enter through the front doors
comment:
Hours are:

Weekdays 9-8

Saturdays 9:30-6

Sundays 11-5

name: Colorado State University Behavioral Sciences Building
directions: Behavioral Sciences Building 1st floor. Located behind Coffee Shop with the male/female bathrooms
comment: Single stall. Locking. Accessible. Yes.

name: Galaxy Theater
directions: Left side, around the corner from the arcade.

name: The Broken Tusk
comment: This is a LGBTQ bar. Very cool place and chill. At the time I went they had a men\'s, women\'s and a gender neutral handicapped accessible bathroom but the owner said he was in the process of making all the bathrooms gender neutral. All three bathrooms have locking doors.

name: The Kettle and Stone Brewing Company
directions: Left side of the hallway, two bathrooms.
comment: This brewery\'s motto is \"All Are Welcome\", and they mean it. The bathrooms are not gender-free by accident. That was an intentional inclusion! The owners are friendly, the beer is amazing, and the bartenders are super cute. Say hi to Caroline!

name: Ravenous
directions: Back of restaurant on the left side
comment: From what I gather they are a very liberal/open-minded staff. One of my favorite servers is openly gay.

name: Saratoga Coffee Traders
directions: Back of store (past coffee counter and candy section) on the left.

name: Price Chopper
directions: Enter the store and go to the right (towards produce). The restroom hallway entrance is in between the two \"Pick 6\" beer coolers. There are traditional gendered restrooms but then there is also a large \"family\" restroom which is genderfree. (and these restrooms are rarely occupied other than by employees, so no guilt if you don\'t actually have kids)
comment: Open 24 hours

name: Black Duck Coffee House
directions: at the back, on the left side of the room.
comment: open 8-5 most days.

name: Atlantic Superstore
directions: Once you go in, go past all the cashiers. Beside the last one there\'s a small aisle that leads to stairs & an elevator. The bathrooms are upstairs. Fully accessible.
comment: Useful if you\'ve just gotten off the bus or train and don\'t want to use the gendered bathrooms in the train station.

name: Honey Bake Shop
directions: Down the hallway on the left side of the room.
comment: Open 9-7 most days. It\'s a small cafe so there\'s no way to sneak in without being noticed, but you might get away with asking.

name: McDonald\'s Restaurant
directions: Walk in the front door and it\'s at the other end of the restaurant directly in front of you, behind a partial wall.
comment: There are two of them, and they are separate!  They are there for anyone and sometimes people come in just to use the bathroom, but the employees will stand at the register anyway just in case you want something!  You do not have to buy anything, though.

name: Subway
comment: This is a regular Subway chain restaurant. Just walk in quickly.

name: Pavement Coffee
directions: When you walk in, it\'s on the right, opposite the register/coffee counter.

name: SW9 Bar
directions: Up the stairs by the entrance door on the left
comment: Safe unsegregated wash area in queer-friendly bar. Five or six stalls have advisory M or W notices, but the stalls are very close together and the notices mostly serve the purpose of stopping cis men from peeing on some of the toilet seats.

name: Univ of Minnesota - Smith Hall
directions: Basement level. Enter lobby elevator. Go down one floor to \"B\" and turn to the right around the corner.
comment: Unisex restroom. Two stalls. Privacy lock with \"occupied\"/\"vacant\" indicator

name: Bravo rotisserie pizzeria
directions: get in the restaurant. go straight. on right, single stalled, genderneutral bathroom. :)  rigt next to it : bigger bathroom for wheelchair accessibility.
comment:
OPENING HOURS : From 11 a.m. to AT LEAST midnight, on most days :D!!!! ---



I love it because it\\\'s a small restaurant and people are so busy with their own stuff, they don\\\'t do anything :) actually , it\\\'s the only public restroom I feel safe of using in my WHOLE TOWN lol :)

name: Latitude 53
directions: First entrance on your right. Accessible bathroom second door on your right.

name: The Boathouse, Forest Park, St Louis
directions: Immediate right after the gate.

name: Transgender Resource Center of New Mexico
directions: There is a sign on the door that lets you know which one is TGRCNM.
comment: TGRCNM is so much more than accessible, gender neutral bathrooms. It is a resource center dedicated to serving the transgender people of New Mexico and our families and loved ones. Come check out all our services and programs, or of course, just come by and use the restroom! The drop-in center is open Monday through Friday 1:00 - 6:00 p.m.

name: Prince Hookah
directions: To the right of the entrance
comment: One small single bathroom.

name: Subway
directions: Past the counter in the hall

name: cafeteria (muddy cup)
directions: at the back past where you order food

directions: There are 4 on campus:  University Center, 2nd Floor; Administration Building near Human Resources; Computing Wing near ITS; Fairlane Center South near Dining Room D.

name: Cinema Muenster
directions: basement
comment: It\\\'s in a cinema, so probably you need to have ticket. There\\\'s are three bathrooms (male, female, transgender/other folk).

name: Mitchell Physics
street: Texas A&M University - Mitchell Physics Building
directions: Second-fifth floor of staff tower.

name: Rudder Auditorium
directions: Family restrooms next to the art.

name: Tiles Park
directions: In the building behind the playground. Labeled \"family\" restroom.
comment: One of the nicest gender-neutral restrooms I\'ve ever seen in a park.

name: Target
directions: Directly to the left of the front entrance, or straight ahead if you take the escalator up.

name: wabigoon rv park
directions: on right side of office
comment:
three gender neutral locking bathrooms, require waking up two steps to get to. Also has a shower.

Are meant for people camping there, but could probably use them if you asked.

name: Idaho Falls Public Library
directions: Through the parking lot entrance, past the reception desk, around the book return area and to the right.  (The person at the reception desk will gladly point it out to you if you ask)
comment: The library has recently added this genderless \"family bathroom\" in addition to the multi-stall gendered bathrooms.

name: Life\'s a stitch
directions: bathroom on left of store
comment: staffed by conservative old ladies

name: Smiley\'s Family Medicine Clinic
directions: just off the lobby
comment: Primarily for patients and their families. This clinic is very respectful, too.

name: Cristol Chemistry Building
directions: Second floor on the east wing of the building. Enter near the CHEM 140 entrance, take the stairs or the elevator upstairs.
comment: Single stall, simply labelled \"restroom\". Door locks securely. Hallway not especially busy but located near staff offices in a well-lit corridor. Not marked as ADA accessible. Signage directs people to the downstairs restrooms, though these are not marked as ADA accessible, and seem no more accessible than the single stalls.

name: Walmart
directions: in front of stores, past customer service and photo dept
comment: frequently occupied

name: Hudson Hotel
directions: Enter at street level at 356 W 58th St, take the escalator up to the lobby. From facing the lobby, turn left to see the elevators, walk towards them, then instead of getting in them, turn right down a hallway and take your first left, there are two genderfree restrooms.
comment: There is a bar behind the check-in desk (where you walk in), so coming in late-ish at night is probably fine! The lobby is pretty cool looking, and the bathrooms are huge for NYC standards.

name: Wilson Library
directions: On the sixth floor, right outside Special Collections.
comment: While you\'re there, check out the library\'s special collections!  They\'ve got a bunch of fabulous old gay stuff from on campus, like \"PROUD\", the gay newspaper on campus in the 1980s.

name: Pottery Barn
directions: You need to ask an employee for a key, the bathrooms are on the lower floor of the store, the stairs are in the back of the store.
comment: There are 2 single occupancy bathrooms total, each is gendered, but the location of them in store (meaning most people will have no idea you just entered or exited the restroom)

name: Safeway
directions: Right side of the store behind the deli.

name: Rexville Market
comment: A nice place to grab a bite to eat if you\'re out cycling.

name: La Conner Library
directions: In the back, near the childrens\' books.

name: Exit 6 Brewery
directions: \"Women\" to the left behind the bar, \"men\" to the right.
comment: The fact that the restrooms are so far apart from each other makes them a bit risky, since going to the \"wrong\" one will be very obvious, but they\'re single-user and the owner is a real friendly guy. Also, try the Vanilla Cream Beer - you\'ll thank me.

name: Breaking New Grounds

name: KRCC-FM

name: Merrill Hall
directions: Second floor, SE part
comment: There are several stalls, but the main bathroom door locks too. Very spacious!

name: The College of St. Scholastica
directions: The first set is in Tower Hall, on the first floor next to the One Stop office.  The second is in the science building on the second floor near the entrance to the tunnel towards Tower Hall.  The other ones are located in the new appartment buildings, Cedar, Scanlon, and Kerst.

name: Capitol Cider
directions: First floor
comment: Somewhat fancy/normy bar, genderfree single-person restroom.

name: Boston Tea Party
directions: At the top of the stairs

name: Casey\'s General Store

name: 3-065 RTF

name: Refuge Cafe
directions: Near the back, labeled \"The Loo Gallery\"

name: In-House Cafe
directions: Back, to the right of the counter.

name: Shell / Smart mart

name: Who Dat Coffee Cafe

comment: 7am-10pm

name: Byrdie\'s

name: Sheetz

name: Starbucks

1st floor Old Main Building, around behind the desk worker

Mercy Heritage Hall/Sullivan

Open Daily: 7am - 8pm

name: USF College of Nursing
directions: Take the elevator to the third floor. Left off the elevator. Left again. Two private, all accessible public restrooms. NOTE: VERY POORLY MAINTAINED.

name: Tamarack Center

name: All Women\\

name: Compton Union Building (CUB)

name: Walter State Community College

comment: Just say you need to pee and they will probably let you in.

name: Tramps

name: Portland Loo (#2)
street: SW Naito Parkway at SW Ash Street
comment:
PORTLAND LOOs are simple, sturdy,

flush toilet kiosks located on sidewalks

in public areas. The loos are free to the public and accessible every day of the year. Portland Loos give the

community environmentally-friendly,clean, and safe restroom facilities.

PORTLAND LOOs are open 24 hours a day,365 days a year

PORTLAND LOOs have handwashing stations mounted on the exterior to serve the pedestrian population PORTLAND LOOs are cleaned twice a day

PORTLAND LOOs are ADA-accessible and can fit a bicycle or stroller comfortably inside.

name: Casa Brandon
comment: Open at night. Trans safe space.

name: Arlington Velo Sport Bicycle Shop
directions: It\'s a little complicated to get there, but you can just ask.  They only have gender-neutral bathrooms, so you don\'t really have to specify that if you don\'t want to.  There\'s a door behind the employee\'s work area, and then there\'s a bit of a maze to go through, but there are two genderfree bathrooms back there!

name: Hanabi
directions: Straight in past the host area to the left.
comment:
Mon-Thur 11am-10pm

Fri-Sat 11am-11pm

name: Maynard Hall, The Ohio State University at Marion

name: UNH Dimond Library
directions: Beside the ATSC/IT Desk
comment: Not yet labeled, just go through the windowed door. Labels coming soon!

name: Starbucks

name: Brooklyn Park Library
directions: Down short hall beyond service desk
comment:
M-Th 9 am - 9 pm
F, Sat 9 am - 5 pm

name: Collectivo Coffee

name: Mother Fool's

Generally, you need to be there for either an event or a class. 

There's a staircase leading up tothe main space so it's not the most accessible.

Also, once there, you'll see two  restrooms but booth of them are unmarked and one of them contains a urinal. Anyone can go to either one.

name: May Day Cafe

name: Starbucks

2 lockable single-person unisex restrooms, with foldaway changing tables.

name: Tropics
directions:
First floor Restaurant
Back
comment: Not Certian but its a bar Restaurant

name: Südblock

comment: I've included these loos under "a safe place".  They are gendered, but they're not heavily used.  So if you're at all comfortable in such a loo, I don't think you'll run into problems here.

name: King House
directions: When you enter through the main door, turn left.  Go all the way to the end and take the door on the left.
comment: I've included these loos under "a safe place".  They are gendered, but are small and not heavily used--unless a big event is taking place.  If you're at all comfortable in such a loo, I think you'll be OK here.

name: Chimichanga
comment: Unisex toilets clean and accessible for customers

name: Bipartisan Cafe
directions: When you walk inside the cafe there are two gender neutral bathrooms at the back of the cafe. One has a picture of an elephant on the door and the other has a picture of a donkey.
comment:
Mon-Fri 6:30am-10pm

Saturday 7am-10pm

Sunday 7am-9pm

Also they make a lot of delicious food. I specifically go there for the homemade pies.

name: Vintage Tex
directions: The bathroom is in the public part of the store, down the hallway on the left.
comment: From the Owner: This is a small vintage clothing store that is usually not too busy. You don't need to buy anything.

name: University of Wisconsin, Madison - Sterling Hall

name: Ninth Street Bakery

Any student will be happy to direct you further given any of these reference points!

name: PH
directions: All floors
comment: corporate

name: Main Street Coffee and News

name: Vermont Thrush Restaurant

name: Top Pot

name: Burgermeister

name: Trader Joe's
directions: In the back of the store

name: Eden Bus Station

name: Charis Books & More

Charis is Atlanta's independent feminist bookstore.



The Charis employees range from ignorant-but-well-meaning to extremely-knowledgeable-and-helpful on trans/gender-varient issues.



In my experience, this bathroom is one of the safest in the city for trans/gender-varient people to use.

Monday  10:30 AM  -  6:30 PM

Tuesday  10:30 AM  -  6:30 PM

Thursday  10:30 AM  -  7:30 PM

name: Rail City Market

name: Michigan Union

name: Petsmart

Everything is made in that facility or at the Bayview Location.

name: Raw Deal
directions: North side of first floor

Technically a public bathroom, just happens to be attached to Esquires, so you are entirely free and entitled to use it.
Happens to be pretty secluded and safe, too.

Third floor turn left

bauhaus has two single stall locking bathrooms, one that has an M and one that has a W but it is very strongly the culture of the regulars to use whatever bathroom is first available/treat them as gender neutral bathrooms, regardless of whatever bathroom people typically use or where they sit on the genderqueer spectrum.



just walk right in. you don\'t have to buy anything. bauhaus employees are some of the nicest people on earth. i go there every day and have only seen them get upset at a customer ONCE, and that\'s because he was harassing me. i love the bauhaus

directions: Walk straight in the main door, turn right at the bamboo curtain.  There is a locking steel door behind which is a very clean and stylish single person unisex bathroom not only equipped with a toilet and urinal, but for some reason there are three chairs in there.  I suspect it doubles as a changing area for staff.
comment: This is one of my top three favorite Vietnamese restaurants, greatly due to its magnificent hours.  It is open until 1am.  It is the only Vietnamese restaurant I've ever been to with a unisex bathroom.  It attracts a very nice crowd.  I've met many nice people there.  Although they do serve alcohol as often as I've been there I've never seen anyone get rowdy.  It seems to be popular with road repair crews and others with late work shifts.  It is also popular with couples.

name: Mosaic Cuisine & Cafe
directions: Bathrooms are just inside the South entrance.  Both entrances are double door vestibules so not so handicap friendly.  However when my Lyme Disease was worse I rode my segway into the place and they didn't give me any grief about parking it inside the restaurant.
comment: The restaurant owner, Theirry Jugnet, and I have discussed many social and political issues, so I even though intersex/genderqeer/transgender rights may or may not have been formally discussed, I tend to assume he supports our needs.  What he has told me included harassment he's received from conservative diners who felt it was somehow inappropriate not to have gender designations on the two individual stalls.  He seems quite proud of how he stood his ground.

name: Germany
comment:
When being in Berlin, you can ride the usual trains by Deutsche Bahn with a usual metro/tram/bus ticket AS LONG AS you're in the area you paid for ( Zone A+B, A+B+C, etc). So if you don't know another toilet, and you have a ticket, and maybe you have to go somewhere anywhere, check out if a train is going that direction instead of taking the subway/bus/train. There are toilets in all trains. They are gender neutral. 
The trains are often unsafe for People of Colour, especcially Black people because we have racial profiling by the police in germany. Also the staff in the trains might be racist, so take care not to get close to someonewearing a uniform.

name: Bread and Roses Food Cooperative
directions: back of store
comment:
Bread and Roses is a safe space that prohibits sexism, cisheterosexism, racism, classism, ableism, and other forms of discrimination. The restrooms are specifically gender-neutral and you do not have to be a paying customer to use them. I *THINK* that at least one of them is wheelchair-accessible, though I'm not sure if there are unforeseen reasons why this isn't the case, so I didn't put it as such (but please correct if I'm wrong!).
The co-op's hours are usually as follows (with some variation since it's staffed by volunteers):
Weekdays: noon-9pm
Weekends: noon-5pm

comment:
We are a kink cafe, so are totally open and welcoming to ALL, regardless of however you define yourself!



You probably should buy something, but if you ask the staff nicely, we are totally understanding of individual situations and will let you use the bathroom!

name: Higgins restaurant
comment: Act like you're eating here

name: University of North Carolina at Greensboro
Student Union Building (SUB)
directions: 3rd floor, North East side of the building beside the AMS Services wing.
comment: There's also a change table.

name: Garden of Eatin' - Gardener's Supply
directions: Through the main door, the restaurant is part of the gardening store and is off to the right (two bathrooms, both unisex).
comment: If it is busy, probably no one will notice if you are just browsing, but it's a good place to buy a cookie or beverage.

name: Crenshaw House
directions: Down the hall towards the back of the building (from the front entrance. I do not think the bathroom is accessible. There are some stairs to get into the front of the building.
comment: Crenshaw is the house for the department of Gender and Sexuality. The professors in the department are awesome and for the most part super trans positive. Probably should be a student, but they are usually super awesome anyway.

name: Ristretto Roasters Nicolai / Schoolhouse Electric
directions: Two single person non-gendered restrooms between the electric shop and the coffee shop in the back
comment: Can most likely just browse a bit and walk in

name: Green Zebra Grocery
directions: Two non-gendered single-room restrooms in the back
comment: Can just walk in & use. I can't actually remember if they are accessible.

name: Come As You Are
directions: At the front of the shop, near the cash desk.
comment: Open and available to all.  Completely accessible w/support bars.

name: Come As You Are
directions: first door on your right, you can't miss it, it's huge.
comment: this is a sex shop - but very queer/woman/body/trans positive and polite :)

name: Saxbys @ Temple University
directions: It is in the back, past the seating.

name: Frontier Field
directions: In the main concourse, ask a staff member if any trouble finding it.
comment: If you reserve a a suite, you get a private bathroom.

name: Avon Free Public Library
directions: Turn left inside front door

name: Pizza Works
directions: 2 Floor (upstairs) to the left
comment: You have to be a paying costumer.

name: MS Cooper Hall, Res Life Offices
directions: Enter the MS Cooper side of the building from the breezeway (handicap access at rear of building), go through the door marked "Residential Life Office" on the far side of the lobby, bathroom is toward the end of the hallway on the right.
comment: MS Cooper Hall outer doors are unlocked 7 days a week from approximately 7am to midnight.

name: Griffith Park @ Shane's Inspiration
directions: Follow directions to the Merry-Go-Round. Drive past the Merry-Go-Round to the farthest parking lot. It's to the North of the parking lots.
comment: 10 stalls, 4 accessible ones. Griffith Park is very popular. They can get overused and dirty on the weekends.

name: UW Oshkosh Halsey Science Center
comment: has changing table

name: UW Oshkosh Halsey Science Center
comment: has changing table

name: Hummus Bros
directions: Ground floor, to the back-right.
comment: A bit of a squeeze, but clean and genderfree. Also, get some takeaway hummus, because OMG it is so good. The guacamole meal is my favourite.

name: Eastview Mall
directions: This is by the restrooms as you enter the main entrance. It\'s a gender-neutral \"family\" bathroom, the kind with a changing table for babies, etc. It has a locking door, and is wheelchair-accessible.
comment: I\'ve used it several times with no problem.

name: Bluestockings (bookstore)
directions: Bathroom is all the way in the back on the right, past the counter.
comment: Website: http://www.bluestockings.com. The people there are either queer or queer-knowledgeable and will probably understand if you need to use a safe bathroom (though it is mad small, approx. the size of a small closet); you don\'t have to buy things. If you have a few minutes and/or a few dollars to spend, though, take a peek through the shelves!

name: EAT
directions: Accessible unisex toilet on ground floor; individual unisex toilets (i.e. with sinks) off common corridor upstairs.
comment: Paying customers only.

name: Western Park
street: Corner of Ponsonby Road and Hopetoun Street
directions: In the park, close to the footpath, corner of Ponsonby Rd and Hopetoun St.

name: IHOP
comment: Have to be a paying customer.

name: Coquitlam Public Library
comment: There isn't technically a unisex gender marker, it's just single stall and has the accessibility symbol on the door.

name: Reading University Library
directions: Library is roughly in the centre of campus, and easily accessed (and signposted) from both Shinfield Rd and Pepper Lane entrances, and the Whiteknights bus stop. The unisex bathroom door is just inside the main entrance.
comment: No student ID required to access.

name: The Buzz Mill
directions: When you walk in the front door, there are two of them directly to your right.
comment: Both bathrooms are gender neutral. Only the one on the right is handicap accessible.

name: Starbucks
directions: on the other side of the bank lobby.
comment: Need to get the key from the Starbucks, hanging on the wall.

name: Alhambra High School
comment: We need restrooms for the transgendered kids, because they get picked on & can't use the restroom, because of their gender.

name: Will Rogers World Airport
directions: Next to Baggage Claim 5 between the two binary restrooms.

name: The Kitchen
directions: On the left as you come in
comment: Signposted 'for customers'

name: chairs
directions: Behind the non - alcoholic bar

name: Boots Bakery and Lounge
directions: Towards the back, on the right and left. Right before the kitchen.
comment: Staff is amazing and very LGBTQQIA friendly!

name: Village Centre Cinemas
directions: Their bathrooms are usually right across from the concession stands and the unisex/gender neutral bathroom is adjacent to the big stalled gendered bathrooms.
comment: I was tickled that they had a gender neutral bathroom as well as the stalled gendered bathrooms. It was awesome! Definitely a great movie experience!

name: Village Centre Cinemas
directions: Their bathrooms are usually right across from the concession stands and the unisex/gender neutral bathroom is adjacent to the big stalled gendered bathrooms.
comment: When I went to this one I was glad to see that the gender neutral bathroom seems to be a chain thing with this theater because both this one and the Wandermere one have them, so I'm very impressed. Go Village Centre Cinemas! :)

name: Molly's Family Restaurant
directions: Bathrooms are all the way in the back past the seating and everything.
comment: I personally, as a transman, have never had problems here but I've known several transwomen who've had issues at this restaurant mostly from staff being rude about them using the women's room.

name: Riverpark Square
directions: Their bathrooms are on the ground floor to the right of the escalators from the front doors and on the third floor up above the food court. Which in that area they have a 'family' bathroom adjacent to the gendered stalled bathrooms.
comment: I prefer the third floor bathrooms because of the 'family' bathroom primarily but even when that is occupied I feel safe going into the third floor gendered stalled bathrooms; whereas I don't feel comfortable going into the ground floor ones.

name: Dollar Tree
directions: The bathrooms are located at the back of the store to the left of the front door.
comment: You need to ask for a key up at the front to get into the bathrooms. They are single occupancy bathrooms but they are gendered. I learned the hard way to ask for the men's room key or they'd automatically give me the women's room key. No one has ever said anything when I phrase it like that, they just hand me the key. But the fact that you have to ask is both frustrating and embarrassing. The bathrooms are safe though and better than most Dollar Tree locations.

name: Costco
directions: Near the regular bathrooms (behind the snack bar)
comment: Coscto membership required

name: The George Hotel
directions: Through double doors in main reception area.

name: New Art Exchange
directions: Up a flight of stairs. Accessible toilets are on ground floor by the cafe.

name: Cafe Nero
comment: Paying customer or very discreet.

name: Muhammad Ali Center
directions: Off main lobby, near auditorium
comment: Either guest or paying visitors. Family restroom.

name: Subway
directions: On the side facing the Genesee River

name: Bodega Bar
directions: The bathroom is directly in the back - single unisex room.
comment: This is a small bar - but when there are a number of people in it, they don't pay much attention. Look like you're looking for a friend in the back, browse the bar menu, leave.

name: Kahvila Pikku Peikko
directions: After you go in, you just have to go to the left and you'll see the door.
comment: You have to either buy something or pay to use the restroom (costs 1 euro or so). Just ask for the key from the shop assistant. The restroom is a small room with one toilet and a sink so it's unisex and for one person at a time.

name: Cartwright Center, UW- La Crosse
street: corner of Campbell Rd. and State Street
directions: on the second floor.
comment: This building contains the university\'s cafeteria and various lounges and offices.  It\'s open in the summer too.  Anyone who looks like they belong on a college campus should have no problem getting in.

name: Western Oregon University
directions: Smith Music Hall by the candy machines in the main hall way of the building.
comment: The Smith Music Hall is closed later in the evening to the public but in general you can go in whenever.

name: Rendezvous Hair Salon
directions: On the left, just passed the counter.
comment: They are really chill there. They'd probably let someone use it even without getting a haircut.

name: mazzoni center (medical practice)
directions: Ask one of the people at the front desk if you can use the bathroom, they have to unlock the door for you
comment: The mazzoni center has a really great trans health program if you're interested

name: fennario coffee & tobacco
directions: Straight back, there's a sign

name: Walmart
directions: Unisex restroom in rear of store near site-to-store counter. Behind electronics section.
comment: Unisex restroom is readily available, but gendered restrooms are also often empty in non-peak hours.

name: Cole's Furniture Center/Auction House
directions: In left side of store.
comment: Single unisex restroom in private corner. Hours change frequently.

name: China Lee
directions: Back of restaurant at the end of long hallway.
comment: Must be paying customer. Two gendered single restrooms tucked in rear of store. Hallway prevents other patrons from seeing which restroom you enter, and are almost always vacant.

name: The LGBT Community Center of Greater Cleveland
directions: Go down the stairs and turn left after the front desk.
comment: One bathroom for people who identify as men and one for people who identify as women. Open to the public.

name: Algebra Tea House
directions: In the back

name: UNLV
directions: Closest cross street are Maryland Parkway and Harmon Ave.  Located in the Student Union building first floor & second floor to the left when you walk in the entrance facing Maryland Parkway.
comment: Hours usually are 7am to 11pm varies on holidays or special events

name: Performing Arts Center at SUNY Potsdam
directions: Downstairs, by the flight of stairs going towards the Crane School (on your left).
comment: Address will not take you to specific building--go down Barrington Drive, the PAC will be on your left if you're entering from Pierrepont Ave.--it's across from Knowles Hall (on your right) and the child care center (which comes up on your left right before the PAC). Very noticeable because the building's design is different from most of the other buildings on campus.

name: Target
directions: Right next to other restrooms at front of store near entrance.

name: Hy-Vee Prairie Trail
directions: Behind Customer Service Counter at the front of the store
comment: Instead of the traditional "stall style" restroom, this grocery store has 8 invidual restrooms. They technically have men/women labels, but I've checked them, and they're all the same- one toilet, one sink, one trash can. There are also two lockable "nursing rooms" with comfy chairs if you ever need a safe place!

name: Pen Centre Mall
directions: There are washrooms tucked away behind the food court.
comment: This is a \'family\' washroom, one of those where anyone can use it and there\'s lots of space. I have never had any trouble using it.

name: Freedom Centre
comment: Only open for safe space sessions and people under 26. But if you're busting and nonbinary and/or trans they'll probably let you in regardless of your age.

name: Gaming Grounds
directions: Go through the door in the back and turn right down the hall. The bathroom is on the left at the end of the hall.
comment:
Closed Mondays, Open daily between 12-8pm

(One of the owners is trans; feel free to say hi!)

name: Prentice Hall KSU
directions: In the Prentice Hall lobby- accessible and gender-neutral bathroom.
comment: Lobby is open from 8am-2am Mon-Thurs, 8am-10pm Fri, 11am-10pm Sat, and 11am-2am Sun.

name: Kent State Wellness Center
directions: first floor family changing rooms by the pool
comment: you must be at least 18 or be accompanied by some one who is and you have to pay the entrance fee  to get past the lobby

name: Farsta Centrum
directions: Upstairs above Burger King
comment: Clean, free, gender-neutral, and very safe/open design in the shopping centre. In a city of few restrooms at all and most requiring payment, and most being gendered, this is great!

name: south point hotel and casino
directions: go to kates corner ice cream bar, follow the wall toward the bar, make immediate left the family restroom is right next to the women's room.
comment: 24 hours

name: claim jumper
directions: family restroom down the restroom hallway

name: Stony Brook University
street: Stony Brook Engineering Light Lab Building
directions: 1st Floor - Near the Southwest Corner

name: Stony Brook University
directions: Basement near the Wellness Center

name: Stony Brook University
directions: One on the 2nd and one on the 3rd floor - near the elevator.

name: Stony Brook University
directions: Basement; 1st, 2nd, 3rd, and 4th Floors - Near Stairwell

name: Stony Brook University
directions: Private bathrooms are located on most floors throughout the building.

directions:
Restrooms in the lobbies of: 
Hendrix College,

directions:
