name: Stony Brook University
directions: 2nd, 3rd, 4th, and 5th floors, across from front elevator

name: Tampa International Airport
directions:
At least 2:

-Airside F, near entrance to Gates 76-90

-1st floor, near American check-in counter & escalators
comment: Restricted to people flying in/out of airport, or meeting someone there; airport security restrictions apply

name: Thwing Center
directions: Adjacent to the Office of Faculty Development and the Cleveland Room, which are up the steps to "Thwing West" (immediately to the left of the street entrance). ADA ramp is about 100 feet further into the building on the same side.
comment: Building is open to the public

name: Tinkham Veale University Center
directions: Located in the part of the building closest to Bellflower Road (it's marked the "Linsalata Entrance"), just past the gendered bathrooms
comment: Building is open to the public (also, this restroom is conveniently located around the corner from Case Western Reserve University's LGBT Center!)

name: Johnson & Wales University
directions: 1st floor by Abbott Park side entrance
comment: Available to: JWU Students, Faculty, Staff or guests, as must have JWU ID to enter building.  Gender Inclusive Single Stalled.

name: El Mundo
directions: Upstairs, past the bar, down a hall to the right.

name: Vendetta
directions: There are two unisex, single-occupancy bathrooms to the right of the bar, with working locks.

name: The Roost
directions: It's across from the counter type seating and between the stairs and the place where you get water. It's cute. They're labeled 1 and 2.
comment: If you come in the door on the corner and head straight  up the stairs (it will be on the left), no one will care.

name: patrick henry mall
directions: Located in the back left side of the food court If entering from the mall . Closed mall entrance is into the food court by Old Navy. Enter the  mall, turn right. Restroom is on the right. This is a unisex/family bathroom, no stalls, exterior door locks securely.
comment: I used this bathroom for years when my kids were young. One of my best friends is a male identifying/male appearing lesbian. She had also used this bathroom with no hassle.

name: PSU Cramer Hall 180
directions: Single Stall in Cramer Hall(CH) 180 at Portland State University.
comment:
More on PSU\'s Gender Neutral Bathrooms at:

PSU\'s Queer Resource Center

http://www.qrc.pdx.edu/



To get involved in bathroom activism email: lowreys@pdx.edu

name: The Family Wash (Restaurant)
directions: Past the stage to the left or the right (there's 2).

name: Planet Fresh
comment: For customers only. Gender neutral, single occupant.

name: Jamba Juice
comment: Customers only.

name: Wolstein Hall
directions: There is one gender inclusive restroom located on each of the building's three floors.  If entering the building from the main entrance, turn left to use the side stairwell.  All three restrooms are located along this stairwell.
comment: CWRU associated

name: Starbucks
comment: Very small Starbucks.  You can walk in and go just a few steps ahead to restroom on left.

name: Subway
directions: Santo Road exit from 52 or Clairemont Mesa Bl exit from the 15.  Strip mall with post office
comment: Can walk straight in front entrance to unisex bathroom.  No key required.  I'd prob feel funny without being a customer though.

name: Charlie's Kitchen
directions: Upstairs in the back. Single stalls with common shared sink. Specifically marked as gender-neutral.
comment: You should be a paying customer.

name: Fred Meyers
directions: Family restroom/ single room between then men's and womens

name: Fred Meyers
directions: Family restroom/ single room between then men's and womens

name: Starbucks
directions: The bathroom is in the back right corner of the cafe. When you walk in the door, look straight ahead and you'll find it.
comment: Not the cleanest bathroom, but oh well.

name: The Wallflower
directions: At the back of the dining area.
comment: For paying customers. While the bathroom itself is accessible, getting through the dining space to it is a bit hard.

name: Khol's
directions: In customer service behind the boy's department.
comment: Restroom says "Family" on door, however the workers won't stop a single person from going in.

name: Acme Lowcountry Kitchen
directions: To the left of the inside bar pass the hostess stand.
comment: Single stalled male restroom and single stalled female restroom.

name: The Outlets at Legends
directions: In the hallway by Ann Taylor and Bose. There is another bathroom by Guess that probably has a unisex option, but I am only certain of the first.
comment: Open to anyone, further down the hallway than expected. It is a "family/handicapped" bathroom.

name: Kansas City ZOO
directions: Discovery Barn, Tropical House, Africa section by the resturaunt, and porta potties in other location

name: Independence Events Center
directions: Right below section 107
comment: Been to many Hockey games dressed up and always been able to use this family restroom

name: The Hop
directions: In the seating area. They are single occupancy (2 of them) with handle locks. The doors are marked with both "male" and "female" symbols.
comment: I am at The Hop ALL the time and Greg (current owner) is awesome and was like "Why are these gendered bathrooms? Let's get rid of that..." and changed them from 2 single-occupancy gendered bathroom, to unisex bathrooms!

name: Jo-Ann Fabrics
directions: In the back of the store next to the women's restroom

name: University of Wisconsin-Waukesha
directions:
Commons 134.

Bathroom is marked with a unisex bathroom sign. Down the hallway for C126-132 that leads to parking lot 2. Across the hall from the LGBTQIA Resource Center.

name: Java Monkey
directions: inside the coffee shop, in the back. there are two single occupancy locked bathrooms. one says 'guys/girls' and the other says 'girls/guys'

name: Balsam Bagels
directions: [At Winton and Balsam St., two blocks north of Blossom Rd.] The restroom is single-user, at the front right of the shop as you enter.

name: Westfield Galleria at Roseville
directions: Off the food court area, over by Rubio's Tacos.
comment: There's a family bathroom, but you have to go through the "family lounge." In the women's bathroom there's an accessible room/stall which is labelled as unisex.

name: Luke 'n Ollie's Pizzeria
directions: To the left down the hall all the way in the back
comment: Single gender neutral bathroom

name: Target
directions: At the front of the store, behind the registers.
comment: The sign on the door says "family restroom"

name: Target at Grossmont Center
directions: Upstairs next to the (multi-stall) gendered restrooms. There are also single stall gendered restrooms downstairs near electronics.
comment: If you can't find it, ask an employee. Target is one of the safest places for trans people and I'll always use the restroom there before anywhere else.

name: The Board and Brew
directions: At the end of a twisty hallway in back, two single-occupancy gender-neutral restrooms.

name: Coffee Break
comment:
Open Su-Th 7am-2am, F-Sa 7am-3pm



Two single stall bathrooms (1 male 1 female) but the crowd is pretty liberal so going into either is pretty safe.

name: Adams Avenue Book Store
directions: One at the back on the bottom floor, another to the left on the second floor.
comment: No need to ask first or buy anything to use the restrooms here :)

name: kano reid
directions: Back of store on the left hand side

name: Blackburn College
directions: There are four on campus. This restroom is in the basement of Stoddard a resident dorm on campus.
comment: Although, this is behind locked doors to anyone who does not live in the residence hall. On Wednesday starting at 9pm if you knock really loud, someone will probably let you in. (GSA meeting time)

name: AWARE Centre
directions: Enter through the main door, straight to the back.
comment: AWARE is the Association of Women for Action and Research. Its staff are really friendly, just say that you need a gender-safe bathroom and it's all good. (:

name: Oogachaga Centre
directions:
By public transport: 
-Chinatown MRT station, exit A, opposite The Tin Tin Shop.
-We're on the third floor (staircase access only, sorry).
comment: Oogachaga is an LGBTQ counselling & support service. As it's a working office, we're only open to visitors on Mon-Fri, 11am - 6pm. We're usually closed on weekends & public holidays.

name: The Cider Pit
directions: All the way to the back
comment: From staff: "Paying customers preferred, but we're not fussed."

name: Walmart (Henrietta)
directions: In the back of the store

name: The Treehouse
directions: On the top floor there's a restroom with two cubicles. One cubicle is marked as for use by women; the other is marked for use by anyone.
comment: The cafe is amazing.

name: Blackburn College - Olin Science Building
directions:
Once you arrive on campus there are two ways to get to this bathroom. 

1. Go to the back of campus to the building at the top of the hill across a bridge. This is the Olin Science Building. Once you go through the doors take a left and there should be two unisex single stalls on the left. 

2. Once on campus head through DCC and toward Bothwell ( the music and theater building). Toward your right there is Mahan. Mahan is connected to Olin. Once inside Mahan there is a big atrium go to the right toward two doors that say "fire door keep closed". Then walk about 10 feet until you see a hallway to the right and take it. Then continue walking until you get to the end of that hall. Once there the hall way comes to a "T" with the main Olin door to the left and a Physics lab to the right. The restroom is right in front of you.
comment: This building is unlocked at 5am and generally locks back up at 10 or 11 pm.

name: Townline Garage
directions: In the waiting room to the left of the lobby, the bathroom is in the corner.

name: Blackburn College -Butler Hall
directions: Once on Campus head toward butler hall on the south side of DCC and go into the north door on the dorm. Then go into the basement and walk about 20 feet until you see a water fountain and some vending machines. Take a right. And they should be right there.
comment:
You need a key for the dorm after 5pm. The north door is locked after that. 

The restrooms have locks on the inside of the door so you can make sure no one comes in while you're doing your business.

name: North Station
directions: Inside North Station at the Commuter rail station, around the corner from the McDonalds/Dunkin\'Donuts by the TD Garden Pro Shop.
comment: Not many people realize this bathroom is here!!!

name: Dough Empire
street: 55 Lorong L Telok Kurau, #01-59/61 Bright Centre
directions: By the outdoor public carpark, next to the staircase.
comment: It's a public restroom. Doesn't always have toilet paper, so bring your own paper.

name: Too Soul Tea
directions: It's right next to the counter

name: Grassroots Books
directions: Towards the back of the store

name: The Garden Slug
street: 55 Lorong L Telok Kurau, #01-59/61 Bright Centre
directions: Around the corner, next to the staircase.
comment: It's a public restroom, so you don't have to be a paying customer.

name: Fred Meyer
directions: By the regular restrooms - behind Starkbucks (Grocery entrance)

name: Target
directions: Left has side of the store as you walk in - by the regular bathrooms

name: Coddington Mall
directions: Macy's end of the mall - down the hall between Payless Shoe Source and Fye

name: Permaculture GTA "10"
directions: Downstairs to the right.
comment: The bathroom in our Garden Center's Office is gender neutral. Free to volunteers and travellers. If locked call 416-858-1454

name: LGBT Community Center
directions: Gender-free bathroom downstairs requires user to get a key from the front desk. The building also has signes posted about all bathrooms being free to use regardless of gender-expression, or something like that.

name: Baobab Cafe
directions: Out the back on the left side, past the counter

name: Newtown Community & Cultural Centre
street: corner of Rintoul and Colunbo St
directions: down corridor to the left
comment: public bathroom - usually only open between 9am and 3p during the week

name: atrium on bay food court
directions: Bottom floor at the west end of the mall (near McDonalds). Just past the entrances to the gendered bathrooms
comment: One single occupancy genderless accessible bathroom. Has baby changing table, as well as acessiblity features. Usually quite clean. Never had a problem here.  Womens gendered bathroom is multi stall.. Fairly safe aside from some odd looks.

name: Target
directions: By the Pharmacy
comment: It is a single room family restroom. Currently out of order but should be fixed soon!

name: Laughing Planet Cafe
directions: You enter and the counter is on the right, the restrooms are to the left. There are 2, both unisex.

name: Lim Chhour Food Court and Supermarket
directions: Just outside the supermarket, behind the glasses shop, through a door toward the car park. Back left corner of the food court.

name: Sturlugata, 101 Reykjavik, Iceland
directions: Ground floor of physics building.

name: Walmart
directions: "Family Restroom," in the back by the gendered restrooms behind the electronics section.

name: Legendary Waters Resort & Casino
directions: On the main floor to the left of the check-in desk, in a hallway behind the vending machine. There's also one in the casino.
comment: It has a shower and a needle disposal box inside.

name: Herburger's
directions: In the front right corner of the store, by the gendered restrooms.
comment: It has a diaper changing station.

name: Wegmans (Calkins Road)
directions: To the right of the main entrance in between the gendered bathrooms.

name: Shoppes on Market
directions: at the back of the first floor (if I remember correctly)

name: Bureau Discriminatiezaken Kennemerland
comment: Restrooms shared with more NGO's, in the building named 'De Pletterij'.

name: Venice Pizza
directions: Go through the kitchen area to the very back, where you'll see a sink, and then turn around and there it is. It's just a little bathroom.
comment: The basil pesto pizza is really good.

name: Scrugham Engineering and Mines building at the University of Nevada, Reno
directions: The building is off the north end of the quad. The bathroom is on the 4th floor at the end of the hall.
comment: I'm not sure if students are supposed to use this restroom, but there were no signs saying otherwise. I'm not sure if it is always unisex, there was a handwritten note on the door designating it as such.

name: Concordia University, EV Complex
directions: Every floor. The one on the first floor is across from the lobby, down the hall a bit from the security desk.

name: Wellness AIDS Services, Inc
directions: Entry is in the back on 4th street.  it is an HIV testing site so you can get free condoms and a test while you are there.  Bathroom is locking and is a one at a time gender neutral bathroom. A very TRANS friendly location.
comment: Open Monday thru Thursday from 9-6pm and on Fridays for those in need from 10-2

name: Joliet Junior College
directions: J building, all floors

name: Cocoa Cinnamon
directions: Accessible rr has outside entrance on side of building. Both inside & outside rrs are unisex.

name: Duke Chapel
directions: Basement level, off parlor.
comment:
One is sometimes marked "women" but has a single stall + locking exterior door. 
Both restrooms have grab bars, but there is no ramp entry to that level + fairly narrow hallways.

name: Valero

comment:
Hours

Mon-Sat: 10am-9pm

Sun: 12pm-6pm

name: Oolong flowerpot
directions: Just past the counter before the stairs on the right.
comment: I've never had to pay to use the bathroom, i've never had a problem bringing my transgender friends with me there (I am trans myself), the only negative is that the bathroom is unusually small. Not recommended for claustrophobic people. Better go to Accents cafe a few doors down for larger, wheelchair accessible, gender neutral bathrooms.

name: (Mandela House) House 6, Trinity college.
directions: Mandela house/house 6 is located to the left off the main entrance jut after you walk through it, characterised by a large black door that is usually open during college term hours. Climb two flights of stairs (present at the entrance to the building by the door) and turn right, walk around the stairwell, and there will be a corridor that turns left. The bathroom is located to the right of where this corridor begins.
comment: It is usually open during the daytime, and during college term. During college term, it may be open later into the evening, but generally remains closed during the summer as far as i know, you may have better luck than I did. It is a college bathroom, so no need to pay.

name: Arts Building, Trinity college, College Green, D2
street: Arts Building, Trinity college, College Green, D2
directions:
Directions to the building:
-from the Nassau st entrance: enter through the Nassau st entrance, follow the passage to the right until you reach the end of it, before the slope into a small green/square/area. The building on your right is the Arts building. Enter it, on the right you will see a security desk, if the bathroom is locked, ask them or the nearest security person to open it. I've asked them to open it because I preferred gender neutral bathrooms and they respected this. on the presumption that the bathroom is open (which it usually is), continue straight ahead, until you reach a small corridor on your right, turn right and there will be the wheelchair accessible bathroom. 

From the main entrance: entering from the main entrance, continue in a straight line heading for the bell tower/double arch that is in the centre of the square. Turn right once you reach this point, and continue in a straight line after this, past the old library on your left and past the secondary square/green area and up the slope (there will be a slope to your left, while there is a wheel chair accessible bathroom this way, it is in the same building, more difficult to access and almost always locked, my advice is to continue straight ahead unless you have an appointment in the lower floor of this building). Once you have entered the building, with the security desk on your right, follow the initial intsructions I gave.
comment: It is almost always open, but if it is not, ask the security to open it. if you prefer gender neutral toilets and do not use a wheelchair, and they question your need for it, state that your preference is a gender neutral toilet, and they should assist you. Complain if they don't.

name: Athens Health Department
directions: Right inside the front door. You walk past the front help window.

name: College for Creative Studies
directions: There are two gender-neutral restrooms in the Kersierge-Ford building, or the "tinkertoy building". It's a big brown and tan building located at the end of the sculpture garden on the College for Creative Studies campus. Go through the bistro/cafeteria on the ground floor until you find two single stall restrooms. You can also walk through the entrance near the yellow sign that tells you the building's name and it will be in the hall on the right hand side.
comment: Only students, staff, and visitors should use this restroom. It is a secure campus and you will be asked for ID if you're on the premises.

name: Duke/Duchess Shoppe
directions: Back of store, directly across from entrance
comment: Bathrooms are CLEAN!

name: Agriculture & Biology Systems Engineering Building - NDSU
comment: It is single use and lockable. It is fully operational from 8 AM to 9 PM during the University's school year and 7 AM to 4 PM during the summer. The building does not have a numbered address but it can be found across Morrill Hall and next to Ladd Hall.

name: Alba Bales House - NDSU
directions: Located on the first floor, room 199.
comment: One single use, lockable stall. Fully operational from 9 AM to 5 PM for the public/staff at NDSU. This building is a "Safe Zone" and houses the Equity and Diversity Center as well as LGBTQ programs.

name: The University of Texas at Austin- Jester Center
directions: As you go to enter the Jester West Dorm from the second floor, it's in an alcove with vending machines directly across from the piano lounge.
comment: Not accessible 11pm-6am due to emergency alarms

name: Memorial Union - NDSU
directions: It is in the first floor in room 172.
comment: It is open from 9 AM to 9 PM during the school year and 7:30 AM to 4 PM in the summer. There is one stall that is lockable.

name: Images Pittsburgh
directions: Rear of the building...3 seperate locking bathrooms

name: Starbucks
directions: Two single stall unisex restrooms in the back of the store

name: Alami

name: NUS University Town - Many Restroom Locations!
directions: Steven Riady Centre - unisex bathroom on 1st and 2nd floors. Education Resource Centre - unisex bathrooms on every floor (1, 2, and 3). They are usually very clean and the door opens directly into the corridor. They are disabled/accessible restrooms as well, and they are usually marked with "wheelchair" signs, so if you see one, you're good to go. There's a neutral, one-stall bathroom wherever you see one.

comment: Has boat hire, coffee shack and bitey swans!

street: 5500 North St. Louis Ave. Building D
directions: Enter the doors where Enrollment Services/Financial Aid/Cashier are located in the D Building. Go down one floor using the stairs or the elevator. Follow the signs for the Counseling Office. The bathrooms are on the left in this short hallway, just past the Counseling Office.
comment: Generally available 8:30 am to 5:30 pm Monday through Friday

name: College for Creative Studies - Art Center Building
directions:
The restroom is labeled as "women". It's on the ground floor of the Art Center Building, which is a dormitory. Go past the elevator next to a big, very old mirror and keep going until you find a small wooden door. I think it's near the stairs. You'll know it when you see it. If you overlook it, ask the person at the lobby's desk. I am unsure if the men's room on the ground floor is a single stall, and I haven't been to it yet, so I don't know. 

The door is too narrow to fit most wheelchairs and the bathroom is small. The building is very old and that part of it hasn't been updated for accessibility.
comment: You have to be a student or a visitor to College for Creative Studies.

directions: Gender-neutral single stall bathrooms

comment: Restrooms are located in the information and ticket sales lobby, and are thus only available during business hours. While LTD does offer traditional multi-stall, gendered restrooms in this location, they also provide a unisex-wheelchair accessible 'single user' restroom with a locking door.

name: Saint Vincent dePaul Thrift Store (River Road/Division)
directions: The Saint Vincent dePaul thrift store is located on Division Avenue, off River Road near the Fred Meyer and Albertsons (just north of Beltline). The restrooms are located in the center-back section of the store, near the fitting rooms.
comment: The restrooms at this location are gendered, single user restrooms with locking doors. The women's room is a spacious, presumably wheelchair accessible room, with the tiniest toilet ever. (it's actually pretty awkward unless you're a child) The restrooms aren't generally well kept here, but if you have to go... it's an option.

name: Virgin Megastore
directions: top floor (3rd), in the corner
comment: gendered but single-stall and locking. very out of the way location, open late 10-11pm

name: Starbucks

comment: Open 24 hours. You have to ask one of the baristas for the door code.

name: Nordstroms
comment: Each stall is it's own individual room!  And a luxurious lounge area to chill out and primp.  Love it.

comment: Noon to 7 weekdays, 10-7 saturday and noon to 6 weekends; often open later for special events.

comment: No one here minds anyone using either bathroom, I've seen hipsters with beards that rival Gandalf's use the woman's restroom.

comment: This restroom is a large, single-user, wheelchair accessible, unisex restroom. It is the only customer restroom in the store. It is not what I'd call "well maintained", and is generally not the cleanest it could be, because children use the restroom alone.Still, there is almost always plenty of toilet paper, paper towels, soap, etc.

Officially only open to students and staff at the university, though in reality there's nothing to stop anyone wandering in. 

Also be aware of the gender neutral toilets on the ground floor of the students union building, which are a 2 minute walk away.

name: UoM Student Union
street: Steve Biko Building, Oxford Road, M13 9PR
directions:
Basement. If entering through the front door, downstairs and down the hall on the left.

If entering from the down-ramp at the rear, down the hall to the left.
comment:
Look like you know what you\\\'re doing.  In the evenings, you may not be allowed downstairs without a gig ticket, as it is also a music venue.



Used to be gendered bathrooms.  They\\\'re now both labelled as \\\"Gender Neutral Bathroom\\\" even though one has urinals.  Only older students remember which is which.

name: Pret, regent st

comment: Have to ask to go through, seems to be open all the time though.

There are two gendered, multi-user restrooms at the front of the store by the checkouts, ignore those. The "Family" restroom is located in the rear of the store, near the shoe/luggage department. (to the left of the refrigerated groceries and Baby clothes, to the right of the electronics/media sections. - There's a large "RESTROOMS" sign on the wall). 

This area is like a second "Customer Service" area, and has three restrooms, a multi-user female, a multi-user male, and a single-user unisex restroom. All three are Wheelchair accessible.
comment: The Unisex restroom is a large, single-user restroom, which is definitely large enough for a wheelchair. This restroom seems to be very well maintained. In the evenings, this area is often cluttered with carts full of 'go backs' and such, but I believe the restroom is still accessible during the later hours.

comment:
I am not certain if it's handicap accessible but there are no steps.

You may want to call to check that they're open. (513) 272-2002  I don't know if you can get in without someone greeting you at the ticket 
booth or concession stand, since this place is so small. You may still be able to get to the restroom without buying a ticket since they don't collect tickets until you get deeper into the theater. I returned after a show in a small group and no one asked for our tickets.

This is a small artsy theater in an upper middle class area. They serve wine and fruit in their concession stand. The staff were friendly, even when I wasn't passing. It's on the main square in the middle of the strip mall. There's parking in the center of the square.

name: Marie Mt Hall

comment: It is single occupancy and has a locking door. The bathroom is a converted gendered restroom, though it is obvious that it was once a men's restroom. The campus LGBT+ center is on that floor, so it gets some traffic.

name: Gundagai Carberry Park

street: 272 Water St, St John's, NL A1C 1B7
directions: Walk to the right when you first get in, go up the stairs to the second floor, they will be to the right

name: Hughes Hall
directions: Just inside the South doors to the building. Immediately on the right hand side of the foyer.
comment: It's a unisex bathroom with a locking door.

name: Lutheran School of Theology at Chicago
directions: Second floor North end of East wing has a gender-free restroom that is not handicap accessible. The East side of the center wing has a handicapped accessible gender-free bathroom.

name: Norris University Center & Gender and Sexuality Resource Center
directions: Located on the 2nd floor of Norris University Center, next to the Louis Room main entrance (there are another set of doors in the rear, the main doors are in the elevator hallway).  A map can be accessed here: http://www.northwestern.edu/norris/about-us/floor-plans/index.html

name: First Congregational UCC Church
directions: Main floor next to Choir room and behind the kitchen in the rear of the church
comment: I am a member of an LGBT chorus and we rehearse at this church. The church is also officially affirming and welcomes all regardless of orientation or gender identity and expression.

name: Le Cagibi
comment: This is one of my favourite cafe's in Montreal - the fact that their bathrooms are genderfree just makes me like them even more.  Staff is very queer friendly.

name: Castro Country Club
directions: Bathroom is now opened by a buzzer behind the counter.  Effectively the same as asking for a key.
comment: Currently under construction (2/7/14)

name: UMBC Commons
directions: Commons Building, ground floor near the Yum Shoppe and Women\'s Center
comment: The bathroom in the UMBC Commons has recently had a few changes, and now just has a single toilet, instead of two separate stalls. There are two of these bathrooms, one on either side of the staircase. The changes were made to help ensure that people knew that it was a single use bathroom.

name: Market Street Coffee
comment: Possibly one of the prettiest bathrooms in Chapel Hill, it\'s just a one-room with a lock that has a gorgeous decorative finish.

name: Swissbakers
directions: Right of the counter, first left down the hall

name: 117 Chapel Street
directions: Towards the back on the left
comment: No need to buy anything

name: Brookfield Fashion Center Shopping Center catherines
directions: In dressing room

name: cousins sybs
directions: Back of resturant

name: The Goodwood Institute
directions: Through the bar behind the book case.
comment: Gender-neutral bathroom with no urinal and three individual stalls, one of which is accessible.

name: Spokane Community College
directions: 3 different bldg on campus come to Bldg 6 Rm 115 to find the locations

name: CSUDH
directions: Loker Student Union, in the food court section towards the bar. They're right next to each other on the right hand side
comment: After 3 years at CSUDH these are the only gender neutral bathrooms I've found that are always unlocked, but they're very nice and rarely used. They are two very large very accessible restrooms complete with a bench to sit on and a lock on the door. There is never a wait, I feel as if most of the students don't notice them at all.

name: Walmart Neighborhood Market (in Gateway Mall center)
directions: This Walmart "Neighborhood Market" is located to the south of Target (in the old "Circuit City" building). The "Family Restroom" is just to the right of the Pharmacy area, on the right-hand wall as you enter the store.
comment: This is a large roomy single-user, unisex restroom with a diaper changing station and wheelchair access. A makeshift sign on the door when I visited indicated that this restroom was open from 6am(or 8am?)-10pm. Gendered, multi-user restrooms are available on the back wall of the store during the off hours.

name: Immaculate Consumption
directions: Walk in from the street and go to the back right corner, through the bead curtain.
comment: Don\'t mind the religious-inspired name, these are cool people. They also have good tea, coffee, and hot chocolate!

name: Cool Beans Cafe
directions: Go right upstairs.
comment: One room bathroom with no gender indication.

name: On street
directions: Near the corner of liebig st, small building on the footpath.
comment: Genderless automatic self cleaning

name: 1369 Coffeehouse Inman Square
directions: Grab a key (at ~knee-height just pass the espresso machine) and head to the back. The sign on each door matches the key-handle that goes with it.

name: 814 Club
comment: Gay Bar with drag shows on Sunday nights

name: Rochester Institute of Technology, Kate Gleason College of Engineering
directions: Go to the entrance of room 2370. It is a few feet to the east. Very easy to miss.
comment: Single-person

name: Rochester Institute of Technology, The Commons
directions: It's on the first floor. Go to the College Grind coffee shop. Follow the hallway that is to the right of stairway that leads to the dining halll.

name: Aplus/Sunoco Gas
directions: Turn immediately right once you enter store. Will be at the end of a short hallway.

name: People's Cafe
directions: ground floor, in the back

name: feather and stone
comment: Two single gendered and two single unisex.  The owners are awesome.  A safe pee for all.

name: Northeastern University: West Village H
directions: Second and third floor has genderfree single-stall locking bathrooms.

name: The Company House
directions: Downstairs, there are six single use gender neutral stalls.

name: FRED
directions: You walk in, there\'s a cafe counter. Go behind the wall that says \"WHET\" (as in \"whet\" your appetite) on it. There\'s 2 bathrooms, both GN and both single stall locked.

name: The Thinkery
directions: Second floor, across from women's restroom
comment: Must be paying customer to enter The Thinkery.

name: Office Building at 79 Main Street
directions: Ground floor by the acupuncture office, and second floor at the top of the stairs.
comment: This is an office building for health care professionals but no one has ever questioned me for coming in just to use the bathroom. Closed on the weekends.

directions: Grose Hall: Located on the main level

directions: Ivers: Located on 3rd floor

directions: Jones: Located on 3rd floor

directions: Library: Near Main Entrance

name: Center for LGBT Health/Kaladi Bros. coffee
directions: Queerly gendered restroom. Two single stall locking restrooms labeled Kenneth and Barb, both drag queen barbie dolls. It is safe to use either restroom

name: Worcester Art Museum
directions: Go in through the entrance on Lancaster St (the one with all the stairs) and head straight back.
comment: It's outside the actual museum galleries, so you don't have to pay to get in.

name: Park Ave Coffee
directions: Walk in and it's past the counter and slightly to the left by the sugar station

name: Dean College
directions: When walking into the Campus Center, go upstairs. If walking up the main staircase, turn left. There will be a small hallway after the Golder Room, with two single unisex bathrooms.
comment: Technically, the restrooms on campus are for students and faculty, but no one will know if you are a student or not. Plus, we are a theatre and dance school, so restrooms are open to the public during performances anyway.

name: Intu Uxbridge
comment: It is a disabled toilet so someone may question it but that would be very rude of them so it is unlikely

name: Pavement Coffeehouse
directions: Two roomy unisex single stall bathrooms available in the back right of the cafe. No key needed. I've gone to them without purchasing anything a number of times.

name: Williams Center, SUNY Fredonia
directions: Nearest to the entrance on the academic side of the building, on the ground floor.
comment: Most buildings on campus have a gender neutral bathroom, or single stall gendered bathrooms.

name: Vidal Sassoon salon
comment: You have to be a client and/or paying customer
